(1, 1, '<p><strong>About Kyrgyzstan</strong></p>\n\n<p>Located in Central Asia and only a 3 hour flight from Delhi with a high quality and cheap education, Kyrgyzstan is a great option for Indian students looking to get their MBBS abroad. The quality of life in Kyrgyzstan has been improving rapidly over the last several decades and students can enjoy European living standards and a top quality medical education. Travel in Kyrgyzstan includes buses and taxis as well as flights connecting the northern and southern parts of the country.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Kyrgyzstan is a mountainous country with temperatures in the winter ranging from -5 to -10 degrees Celsius. Temperatures in the summer are warm and mild with highs of 25 degrees Celsius.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>About Medical Education in Kyrgyzstan</strong></p>\n\n<p>Kyrgyzstan’s educational system has a reputation for boosting careers and encouraging future development. The educational system in Kyrgyzstan is extremely developed and is comparable to western countries like the United States, Canada, UK, Australia and others. Medical programs in Kyrgyzstan have been designed for English speaking people so prospective medical students with English language skills can succeed without language barriers in their education. The World Health Organization (WHO) recognizes graduates of Kyrgyzstan medical schools to be qualified to work in any field of medicine. Graduates looking to practice medicine in another country just need to meet the requirements of the medical counsel in their desired country of work. <strong>An MBBS program in Kyrgyzstan will take 6 years of study to complete and there is no entry exam required.&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>Kyrgyzstan has superb medical education, and students also have the opportunity to experience a new country and culture that will make this one of the most memorable experiences of their lives.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>General Medicine, Pediatrics, Pharmacy, Dentistry, and, Surgery are among the most popular fields of study for MBBS in Kyrgyzstan. Kyrgyzstan has always been a leader in surgery, and they have top quality surgeons and doctors.</p>\n\n<p>For students who are looking for a university at which to get their MBBS they should consider visiting Kyrgyzstan. It is one of the most popular places for people looking to get an excellent MBBS education at a low cost.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Benefits of Studying MBBS in Kyrgyzstan</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Getting your MBBS in Kyrgyzstan provides students with many benefits including help in procuring loans and scholarships&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Kyrgyz medical universities offer a high quality medical education for a much lower cost.&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Kyrgyzstan is at the moment the cheapest option in the world for getting your MBBS degree</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Medingo Education supports you from start to finish in getting your MBBS abroad. We will help you pick your university, complete your application and documents, get to your university, and continue to support you throughout your studies.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Eligibility Requirements</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Prospective students must be&nbsp;<strong>at least 17 years and no more than 25 years</strong>&nbsp;by 31st December of&nbsp;the year of their admission to the MBBS course.</li>\n	<li>Students must have a&nbsp;<strong>valid NEET Scorecard. Only NEET Qualified students</strong>&nbsp;can go to study abroad. In 2018 the NEET eligibility score was around 90 to 115 for different categories&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>\n	<li>Any Indian citizen looking to study in an undergraduate medical course in any foreign medical institution must have an Eligibility Certificate issued by the Medical Council of India, New Delhi. To get the Eligibility certificate a candidate must pass 10+2 or equivalent class (biology, physics, and chemistry with minimum 50% marks) from a recognized school.</li>\n	<li>Post-graduation: MBBS degree and one-year internship from a college/university/institution recognized by the government of the country in which you wish to practice.</li>\n	<li>Any additional requirements set by the country in which you wish to practice</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Required Documents</strong></p>\n\n<p>The following documents are to be submitted along with the completed application form</p>\n\n<ol>\n	<li>Matriculation Certificate (10th Class) showing the date of birth</li>\n	<li>Certificate and mark-sheet of Intermediate (10+2 or equivalent class) with minimum 50% of marks are required as eligibility criteria of MCI</li>\n	<li>Six passport sized photographs</li>\n	<li>Photocopy of Passport (if ready)</li>\n	<li>Medical Certificate with HIV test report from the recognized government hospital/pathological lab/clinic</li>\n	<li>Eligibility Certificate from Medical Council of the country</li>\n	<li><strong>NEET Scorecard to verify the NEET Qualification of the student</strong></li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Admission Process</strong></p>\n\n<p><strong>MBBS in Kyrgyzstan </strong>admission is open&nbsp;to all international students who meet the eligibility criteria of the university to which they are applying. Applicants do not have to pass any entrance exams, but they must have a<strong>&nbsp;valid NEET Scorecard</strong>. The course curriculum is set by the Ministry of Public Health and the Ministry of Education Kyrgyzstan.</p>\n\n<p>All completed forms along with attested photocopies of all required documents must be submitted to the universities via the concerned representative.<br>\nAdmission will be confirmed only after the documents and completed application have been reviewed and approval has been granted by the authorized representative of the university.&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Legalization and Translations of Documents</strong></p>\n\n<p>In addition to the requirements above, the following documents must be legalized by the Ministry of Education &amp; Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the country in question and then they will be translated into Russian by an authorized translator from Embassy of Kyrgyzstan:</p>\n\n<ul>\n	<li>Original Certificate &amp; mark sheet of 10th class</li>\n	<li>Original Certificate &amp; mark sheet of 10+2 or equivalent class.</li>\n	<li>Original Degree of MBBS or equivalent (in case of PG candidates only)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p><strong>Is it safe for Indian students in Kyrgyzstan?</strong></p>\n\n<p>There is no country that is 100% safe or completely without prejudice. There is no guarantee that individuals will not experience occasional moments of discomfort prompted by intolerant people. However, intolerance and prejudice are far from the most common trait to be found in Kyrgyzstan. Kyrgyz people are by and large friendly and welcoming to foreigners. With so many Indian students, tourists, and workers in Kyrgyzstan, most Kyrgyz people are used to seeing Indians, however, this does not mean that students won’t at times receive more attention than a local person would. While serious safety concerns are not common, foreigners should still exercise caution especially when it comes to more common things like pick pocketing.</p>\n\n<p>MBBS Education will help train students on how to keep themselves safe in Kyrgyzstan and provide tips/advice for their safety. We will also support students whenever they need help.</p>\n\n\n\n', '#1 MBBS Educational Consultancy for Kyrgyzstan with Free Counselling', 'Do you want to achieve your dream for MBBS study in Kyrgyzstan  Learn about the documents and processing fee from our study consultants at IMC.'),
(1, 2, '<h3>About Bangladesh</h3>\n<p>Bangladesh is a country in South Asia, bordered by India, Myanmar, and the Bay of Bengal. Known for its lush greenery, rich culture, and bustling cities, the capital of Bangladesh is Dhaka. The country has a deep history and is known for its friendly and hospitable people.</p>\n<h3>About Medical Education in Bangladesh</h3>\n<p>Medical education in Bangladesh is becoming increasingly popular among international students. The country has several medical colleges that offer MBBS (Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery) programs in English. These institutions are known for their high standards of education and are recognized by international medical councils.</p>\n<h3>Benefits of Studying MBBS in Bangladesh</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Affordable Education:</strong> The cost of studying MBBS in Bangladesh is lower compared to many other countries.</li>\n<li><strong>High-Quality Education:</strong> Medical colleges in Bangladesh offer excellent education with qualified faculty and modern facilities.</li>\n<li><strong>Global Recognition:</strong> MBBS degrees from Bangladesh are recognized by global medical councils, allowing graduates to practice medicine in various countries.</li>\n<li><strong>English Medium:</strong> Many medical colleges teach in English, making it easier for international students to study.</li>\n<li><strong>Cultural Familiarity:</strong> Bangladesh shares cultural similarities with neighboring countries, making it a comfortable environment for South Asian students.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Eligibility Requirements</h3>\n<p>To study MBBS in Bangladesh, students generally need to meet the following criteria:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Educational Qualification:</strong> Completion of higher secondary education (10+2) with Physics, Chemistry, and Biology.</li>\n<li><strong>Minimum Marks:</strong> A minimum aggregate score of 60% in the core subjects.</li>\n<li><strong>Age:</strong> The applicant must be at least 17 years old.</li>\n<li><strong>NEET Exam:</strong> Qualifying in the NEET (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test) is mandatory for Indian students.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Required Documents</h3>\n<p>Students need to provide several documents for the admission process:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Academic Certificates:</strong> Copies of 10th and 12th grade mark sheets.</li>\n<li><strong>Passport:</strong> A valid passport with at least 18 months validity.</li>\n<li><strong>Passport-sized Photos:</strong> Recent passport-sized photographs.</li>\n<li><strong>NEET Score Card:</strong> For Indian students.</li>\n<li><strong>Medical Certificate:</strong> A certificate showing the student is medically fit.</li>\n<li><strong>Invitation Letter:</strong> Issued by the university in Bangladesh.</li>\n<li><strong>Birth Certificate</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Admission Process</h3>\n<p>The admission process for MBBS in Bangladesh typically involves the following steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Application:</strong> Fill out the application form available on the university\'s website.</li>\n<li><strong>Submission of Documents:</strong> Submit the required documents as listed above.</li>\n<li><strong>Admission Letter:</strong> Receive the admission or invitation letter from the university.</li>\n<li><strong>Visa Application:</strong> Apply for a student visa at the Bangladesh embassy with the admission letter and other necessary documents.</li>\n<li><strong>Travel:</strong> Book your tickets and travel to Bangladesh before the commencement of the course.</li>\n<li><strong>Enrollment:</strong> Complete the enrollment process at the university upon arrival.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Legalization and Translations of Documents</h3>\n<p>For international students, especially from India, certain documents need to be legalized and translated. Legalization typically involves attestation by the Ministry of External Affairs (MEA) and the Bangladesh embassy. Documents like educational certificates and the birth certificate should be translated into English if they are in a different language.</p>\n<h3>Is it Safe for Indian Students in Bangladesh?</h3>\n<p>Bangladesh is generally safe for international students, including those from India. Medical colleges often have good support systems for international students, including safety measures and assistance. It is advisable to follow local laws, respect the culture, and stay informed about any travel advisories. Many Indian students have successfully studied in Bangladesh and found it to be a welcoming and secure environment.</p>', 'Best MBBS Education Consultancy for Bangladesh in India with free counselling | 2024', 'Best MBBS Educational consultancy for Bangladesh  in India with 100% free consultancy. Join IMC MBBS Education Consultancy taught by subject-matter experts now!'),
(1, 3, '<h3>About Russia</h3>\n<p>Russia is the largest country in the world, spanning Eastern Europe and northern Asia. It is known for its rich history, diverse culture, and vast landscapes ranging from tundras to forests. The capital city, Moscow, is famous for its architectural landmarks, including the Kremlin and Red Square. Russia has a significant cultural heritage with contributions to literature, music, and art.</p>\n<h3>About Medical Education in Russia</h3>\n<p>Medical education in Russia is well-regarded globally, attracting many international students. The country has numerous medical universities that offer MBBS (Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery) programs in English. These universities are known for their high educational standards, experienced faculty, and modern facilities, making Russia a preferred destination for medical studies.</p>\n<h3>Benefits of Studying MBBS in Russia</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Affordable Tuition:</strong> The cost of studying MBBS in Russia is relatively lower than in many Western countries.</li>\n<li><strong>Quality Education:</strong> Russian medical universities provide high-quality education with a focus on practical skills and research.</li>\n<li><strong>Global Recognition:</strong> MBBS degrees from Russia are recognized by international medical councils, allowing graduates to practice medicine worldwide.</li>\n<li><strong>English Medium Instruction:</strong> Many universities offer courses in English, which helps international students to understand the curriculum better.</li>\n<li><strong>Cultural Exposure:</strong> Studying in Russia offers a unique cultural experience and the opportunity to learn a new language.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Eligibility Requirements</h3>\n<p>To study MBBS in Russia, students generally need to meet the following criteria:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Educational Qualification:</strong> Completion of higher secondary education (10+2) with Physics, Chemistry, and Biology.</li>\n<li><strong>Minimum Marks:</strong> A minimum aggregate score of 50% in the core subjects.</li>\n<li><strong>Age:</strong> The applicant must be at least 17 years old.</li>\n<li><strong>NEET Exam:</strong> Qualifying in the NEET (National Eligibility cum Entrance Test) is mandatory for Indian students.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Required Documents</h3>\n<p>Students need to provide several documents for the admission process:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Academic Certificates:</strong> Copies of 10th and 12th grade mark sheets.</li>\n<li><strong>Passport:</strong> A valid passport with at least 18 months validity.</li>\n<li><strong>Passport-sized Photos:</strong> Recent passport-sized photographs.</li>\n<li><strong>NEET Score Card:</strong> For Indian students.</li>\n<li><strong>Medical Certificate:</strong> A certificate showing the student is medically fit.</li>\n<li><strong>Invitation Letter:</strong> Issued by the university in Russia.</li>\n<li><strong>Birth Certificate</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Admission Process</h3>\n<p>The admission process for MBBS in Russia typically involves the following steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Application:</strong> Fill out the application form available on the university\'s website.</li>\n<li><strong>Submission of Documents:</strong> Submit the required documents as listed above.</li>\n<li><strong>Admission Letter:</strong> Receive the admission or invitation letter from the university.</li>\n<li><strong>Visa Application:</strong> Apply for a student visa at the Russian embassy with the admission letter and other necessary documents.</li>\n<li><strong>Travel:</strong> Book your tickets and travel to Russia before the commencement of the course.</li>\n<li><strong>Enrollment:</strong> Complete the enrollment process at the university upon arrival.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Legalization and Translations of Documents</h3>\n<p>For international students, especially from India, certain documents need to be legalized and translated. Legalization typically involves attestation by the Ministry of External Affairs (MEA) and the Russian embassy. Documents like educational certificates and the birth certificate should be translated into Russian if they are in a different language.</p>\n<h3>Is it Safe for Indian Students in Russia?</h3>\n<p>Russia is generally safe for international students, including those from India. Medical universities often have robust support systems for international students, including safety measures and assistance. It is advisable to follow local laws, respect the culture, and stay informed about any travel advisories. Many Indian students have successfully studied in Russia and found it to be a welcoming and secure environment.</p>', 'Best MBBS Education Consultancy for Russia in India with free counselling | 2024', 'Best MBBS Educational consultancy for Russia in India with 100% free consultancy. Join IMC MBBS Education Consultancy taught by subject-matter experts now!'),
(1, 4, '<h3>About Nepal</h3>\n<p>Nepal is a beautiful country located in South Asia, nestled in the Himalayas between India and China. Known for its stunning mountain scenery, including Mount Everest, the highest peak in the world, Nepal offers a rich cultural heritage with diverse ethnic groups and traditions. The capital city is Kathmandu, which is famous for its historic temples and vibrant culture.</p>\n<h3>About Medical Education in Nepal</h3>\n<p>Medical education in Nepal is gaining popularity among international students, particularly those from neighboring countries. Nepal has several reputable medical colleges that offer MBBS (Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery) programs. These colleges are known for their high educational standards, experienced faculty, and well-equipped facilities. The medium of instruction is often English, making it accessible for international students.</p>\n<h3>Benefits of Studying MBBS in Nepal</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Affordable Tuition:</strong> The cost of studying MBBS in Nepal is relatively lower compared to many other countries.</li>\n<li><strong>High-Quality Education:</strong> Medical colleges in Nepal provide quality education with a focus on practical skills and research.</li>\n<li><strong>Recognition:</strong> MBBS degrees from Nepal are recognized by global medical councils, enabling graduates to practice medicine in various countries.</li>\n<li><strong>English Medium:</strong> Many medical colleges in Nepal offer courses in English, facilitating better understanding for international students.</li>\n<li><strong>Cultural Similarity:</strong> Nepal shares cultural and geographical proximity with India, making it easier for Indian students to adapt.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Eligibility Requirements</h3>\n<p>To study MBBS in Nepal, students generally need to meet the following criteria:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Educational Qualification:</strong> Completion of higher secondary education (10+2) with Physics, Chemistry, and Biology.</li>\n<li><strong>Minimum Marks:</strong> A minimum aggregate score of 50% in the core subjects.</li>\n<li><strong>Age:</strong> The applicant must be at least 17 years old.</li>\n<li><strong>Entrance Exam:</strong> Qualifying in the entrance exam conducted by the medical colleges or universities in Nepal.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Required Documents</h3>\n<p>Students need to provide several documents for the admission process:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Academic Certificates:</strong> Copies of 10th and 12th grade mark sheets.</li>\n<li><strong>Passport:</strong> A valid passport with at least 18 months validity.</li>\n<li><strong>Passport-sized Photos:</strong> Recent passport-sized photographs.</li>\n<li><strong>Entrance Exam Score:</strong> Scorecard of the entrance exam conducted by the college or university.</li>\n<li><strong>Medical Certificate:</strong> A certificate showing the student is medically fit.</li>\n<li><strong>Invitation Letter:</strong> Issued by the university in Nepal.</li>\n<li><strong>Birth Certificate</strong></li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Admission Process</h3>\n<p>The admission process for MBBS in Nepal typically involves the following steps:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Application:</strong> Fill out the application form available on the university\'s website.</li>\n<li><strong>Submission of Documents:</strong> Submit the required documents as listed above.</li>\n<li><strong>Entrance Exam:</strong> Appear for the entrance exam conducted by the university.</li>\n<li><strong>Admission Letter:</strong> Receive the admission or invitation letter from the university.</li>\n<li><strong>Visa Application:</strong> Apply for a student visa at the Nepalese embassy with the admission letter and other necessary documents.</li>\n<li><strong>Travel:</strong> Book your tickets and travel to Nepal before the commencement of the course.</li>\n<li><strong>Enrollment:</strong> Complete the enrollment process at the university upon arrival.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Legalization and Translations of Documents</h3>\n<p>For international students, especially from India, certain documents need to be legalized and translated. Legalization typically involves attestation by the relevant authorities in India and the Nepalese embassy. Documents like educational certificates and the birth certificate should be translated into English if they are in a different language.</p>', 'Steps To Go Nepal for MBBS Study- IMC Consultancy with free counselling.', 'Check out the whole procedure to study for MBBS at Nepal that will immensely benefit you to study in the global university of your choice! For FREE counseling contact us!'),
