(4, 6, '<p>   Business Management courses refine the management-related skills of a person   necessary to run a business. In other words, Business Management courses   provide detailed knowledge about various aspects of running a business. In   Business Management courses, one learns about the establishment of a company   or an organisation, and various functional levels such as production,   financial, administrative, human resources, sales &amp; marketing, and others. </p> <p>   To be eligible for Business Management courses, candidates must have   passed&nbsp;<strong>Class 12</strong>&nbsp;from a recognised board. The   popular entrance exams that are conducted for Business Management courses   are&nbsp;<strong     >CAT,&nbsp;MAT,&nbsp;CMAT,&nbsp;MAH CET,&nbsp;TISS NET&nbsp;etc.</strong   >&nbsp;The average Business Management course fee ranges between&nbsp;<strong     >INR 50,000 and 25 Lakh.&nbsp;</strong   > </p> <p>   Business Management courses are open to students from&nbsp;<strong     >all streams     &ndash;&nbsp;Commerce,&nbsp;Science&nbsp;and&nbsp;Arts&nbsp;&ndash;</strong   >&nbsp;and can be pursued at&nbsp;<strong     >undergraduate&nbsp;(BBA/BMS), postgraduate&nbsp;(MBA/PGDM)&nbsp;and     doctoral&nbsp;(PhD, FPM)&nbsp;levels</strong   >. Business Management courses help students in building managerial abilities   such as communication, organisation, leadership, reporting, and teamwork. Once   graduated with a Business Management course degree, candidates can opt for job   profiles such as Management Trainee, Sales Representative, Marketing   Executive, Manager, etc. The average salary that a Business Management   graduate earns ranges between&nbsp;<strong>INR 2 - 28 LPA.</strong> </p> <h2><strong>Business Management Courses: Highlights</strong></h2> <p>   The main aim of Business Management courses is to prepare students to apply   management principles in a variety of industrial situations. The Business   Management courses help students gain knowledge of how businesses operate, how   they are managed, and how they interact with one another and their   surroundings. </p> <p>   Desirous students can have a look at the table below to get quick information   about Business Management courses. </p> <table>   <tbody>     <tr>       <th>         <p><strong>Particulars</strong></p>       </th>       <th>         <p><strong>Details</strong></p>       </th>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Course Name</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Business and Management Studies</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Course Level</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>           Undergraduate, Postgraduation, Diploma, PG Diploma, Certification and           Doctorate         </p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Entrance Exams</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>CAT,&nbsp;MAT,&nbsp;CMAT,&nbsp;MAH CET,&nbsp;TISS NET&nbsp;etc.</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Duration&nbsp;</p>       </td>       <td>         <ul>           <li><strong>Undergraduate Courses:&nbsp;</strong>3 years</li>           <li><strong>Postgraduate Courses:</strong>&nbsp;2 years</li>           <li><strong>Certificate Courses</strong>: a few months to 1 year</li>           <li><strong>Diploma Courses:</strong>&nbsp;1 year</li>           <li><strong>Doctorate :</strong>&nbsp;3 years&nbsp;</li>         </ul>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Eligibility</p>       </td>       <td>         <ul>           <li>             <strong>Undergraduate Courses: Passed class</strong>&nbsp;12 with a             minimum of 50% in aggregate           </li>           <li>             <strong>Postgraduate Courses</strong>: Passed class 12 with a             minimum of 50% in aggregate from a recognised board           </li>           <li>             <strong>Certificate Courses:</strong>&nbsp;12th pass or 10th pass             from a recognised board           </li>           <li>             <strong>Diploma Courses:</strong>&nbsp;Graduation from a recognised             board           </li>           <li>             <strong>Doctorate</strong>: Masters Degree or PG Diploma with a             minimum of 55% aggregate           </li>         </ul>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Fees</p>       </td>       <td>         <ul>           <li><strong>Undergraduate Course:</strong>&nbsp;INR: 50K-2 Lakhs</li>           <li><strong>Postgraduate Course</strong>: INR 3-25 LPA</li>           <li><strong>Certificate Courses:</strong>&nbsp;INR 5K-10 Lakhs</li>           <li><strong>Diploma Courses</strong>: INR 5-8 Lakhs</li>           <li><strong>Doctorate</strong>: INR 1-5 LPA</li>         </ul>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Average Salary</p>       </td>       <td>         <ul>           <li>             <strong>Undergraduate Courses:</strong>&nbsp;INR 2.75-8 LPA&nbsp;           </li>           <li><strong>Postgraduate Courses:&nbsp;</strong>INR 3-28 LPA</li>           <li><strong>Certificate Courses</strong>: INR 2-8 LPA</li>           <li><strong>Diploma Courses</strong>: INR 2-8 LPA</li>         </ul>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Job Profiles</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>           Manager, Financial Manager, Business Analyst, Business Development           Manager etc.         </p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Top Recruiters</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>           Godrej, Reliance, TCS, Dell, Accenture, Deloitte, Amazon and so on.         </p>       </td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table> <h2>All About Business Management Courses</h2> <p>   Business Management courses focus on providing an&nbsp;<strong     >in-depth understanding of human resource management</strong   >, economics, new corporate strategy, entrepreneurship, trading, finance, and   risk analysis needed for managerial professions. </p> <p>   The undergraduate Business Management courses&nbsp;<strong     >teach the techniques and theories of management</strong   >. Many colleges and universities, including some famous institutions like   Delhi University, offer Business Management courses. </p> <p>   The Business Management courses career scope of the professional courses is   broad because there are employment chances in industries like banking,   education, and information technology, among others. </p> <h3>Why Study Business Management Courses<strong>?</strong></h3> <p>   Business Management courses are useful tools that can aid in a   candidate\'s&nbsp;<strong>job search for managerial positions</strong>. Also,   Business Management courses offer information to those who are considering   starting their own business. Depending on your long-term objectives, you can   pursue&nbsp;<strong>several levels of study</strong>, from undergraduate to   graduate degrees in business management. Several schools and universities   provide on-campus or online courses, and they have a variety of   specialisations from which students can select according to their preferences. </p> <h2><strong>Business Management Courses: Eligibility Criteria</strong></h2> <p>   Business Management courses are divided broadly into two levels: Undergraduate   and Postgraduate. </p> <table>   <tbody>     <tr>       <th>Courses</th>       <th>Eligibility Criteria</th>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>UG</td>       <td>         <p>Class 12</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>PG</td>       <td>MBA and PGDM</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>PG Diploma</td>       <td>Graduation</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Diploma</td>       <td>No Entrance Exam</td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table> <p>   <strong>Must Check:</strong>&nbsp;Top Datawarehouse Interview Questions and   Answers </p> <h2><strong>Business Management Courses: Entrance Exams 2024</strong></h2> <p>   Most of the business management institutes select candidates for admission on   the basis of entrance exam scores. Some B-schools accept scores of   national-level exams, while some conduct their own entrance exam. We have a   list of the top entrance exams below that are conducted for Business   Management courses: </p> <p>   Students can see the table below to learn important details related to   Business Management courses conducted at the national level or university   level. </p> <table>   <tbody>     <tr>       <th>Name of Entrance Exam</th>       <th>Exam Dates</th>       <th>Exam Schedule</th>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>SET&nbsp;</td>       <td>May \'24</td>       <td>SET Schedule&nbsp;</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>IPMAT&nbsp;</td>       <td>June \'24</td>       <td>IPMAT Schedule&nbsp;</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>CUET&nbsp;</td>       <td>15 May \'24 - 31 May \'24</td>       <td>CUET Schedule</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>CAT</td>       <td>26 Nov \'23</td>       <td>CAT Schedule</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>CMAT</td>       <td>May \'24</td>       <td>CMAT Schedule</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>NMAT&nbsp;</td>       <td>10 Oct \'23 - 19 Dec \'23</td>       <td>NMAT Schedule</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>ATMA</td>       <td>Jul \'24</td>       <td>ATMA Schedule</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>SNAP</td>       <td>10 - 22 Dec \'23&nbsp;</td>       <td>SNAP Schedule</td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table> <p><strong>Also Read:</strong></p> <p>Top Exams for Management Courses</p> <table>   <tbody>     <tr>       <td>         <p>VARC Preparation Tips for MBA Exams</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>DILR Preparation Tips for MBA&nbsp;Exams</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Quantitative Aptitude Preparation Tips for MBA Exams</p>       </td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table> <p>   Want to ace the Hadoop Interview? Check the&nbsp;top 40 Interview Questions   and Answers </p> <h2>   <strong>Business Management Courses and Sp</strong   ><strong>ecialisations</strong> </h2> <p>   Business Management courses are available at UG, PG, PhD levels in regular as   well as distance-education mode. Business Management courses are offered by   government colleges as well as private institutes. Given below is the list of   Business Management courses at various levels. </p> <table>   <tbody>     <tr>       <th>         <p><strong>UG Courses</strong></p>       </th>       <th>         <p><strong>PG Courses</strong></p>       </th>       <th>         <p><strong>Doctoral and Other Courses</strong></p>       </th>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>BBA</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>MBA</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>FPM</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>BBM&nbsp;</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Executive MBA</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>PhD</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>BMS</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Distance MBA</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>MDP</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Integrated MBA</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Part-Time MBA/Online MBA</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Certificate courses in Business Management</p>       </td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table> <p><strong>Also Read:</strong></p> <p>All about Business Management courses</p> <h3><strong>Specialisations in&nbsp;</strong><strong>BBA</strong></h3> <p>   Bachelor of Business Administration is one of the most well-liked options for   a lucrative job (BBA). Students can choose to enrol in the course at a public   or private college. Typically, BBA programmes are designed so that students   gain leadership and business management skills from day one. Check the table   below for list of BBA specialisations offered by institutes, colleges and   universities in the three-year degree course: </p> <table>   <tbody>     <tr>       <th>BBA Specialisations</th>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>BBA Human Resource</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>BBA Banking and Insurance</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>BBA Finance</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>BBA Information Technology</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>BBA Marketing &amp; Sales</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>BBA Foreign Trade</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>BBA LLB</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>BBA Tourism and Hospitality</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>BBA Family Business</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>BBA Organisational Management</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>BBA Digital Marketing</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>BBA International Business</p>       </td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table> <p><strong>Also Read:&nbsp;</strong>Top Specialisations in BBA</p> <h3><strong>Specialisations in&nbsp;</strong><strong>MBA</strong></h3> <p>   Several students obtaining a degree in business management are unsure of the   area of expertise they want to focus on. They frequently learn about the many   management specialisations at the beginning of their education, along with how   they all fit together in a corporate environment. The aspirants can choose   whether they would like to concentrate their study in one particular field or   acquire a more comprehensive understanding of each discipline after having a   deeper awareness of each discipline. Check the table below for list of MBA   specialisations offered by institutes, colleges and universities in the   two-year degree course: </p> <table>   <tbody>     <tr>       <th>         <p>MBA Specialisations</p>       </th>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Finance</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Infrastructure</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Marketing</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>International Business</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Sales</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Disaster Management</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Human Resources</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Energy &amp; Environment</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Operations</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Import &amp; Export</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Product</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>IT &amp; Systems</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Business Analytics</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Healthcare &amp; Hospital</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Digital Marketing</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Business Economics</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Entrepreneurship</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Agriculture &amp; Food Business</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Advertising</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Materials Management</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>NGO Management</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Oil &amp; Gas</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Pharma</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Retail</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Project Management</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Rural Management</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Sports Management</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Supply Chain</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Telecom</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Textile Management</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Transport &amp; Logistics</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Forestry</p>       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>         <p>Public Policy</p>       </td>       <td>         <p>Hospitality</p>       </td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table>', 'Business Management in India', 'Business Management in India');
