(1, 'KYRGYZ NATIONAL MEDICAL UNIVERSITY', 1, '', 1, '<p>   Kyrgyz National University in Bishkek is the oldest and largest higher   education institution in Kyrgyz Republic. Established in 1925 as the Kyrgyz   Institute of Education, it recently partnered with LN University, India, to   launch its Faculty of Medicine. This collaboration marks the first Central   Asian university to have a Faculty of Medicine associated with an Indian   university. </p> <p>   The university now offers a 5-year MD Physician program using LN   University&rsquo;s teaching platform from Bhopal, India. </p>  <h3>The History</h3>  <p>   The Kirghiz State Pedagogical Institute, later known as the Kyrgyz State   University, was founded in 1932. It originated from specialized educational   institutions established in 1925 to address the need for university teachers   in the Kyrgyz Republic. In 1951, the Kyrgyz State University was established   in Frunze based on the Kirghiz Pedagogical Institute. </p> <p>   In 1972, it was renamed as the &ldquo;Kirghiz State University named after the   50th anniversary of the USSR.&rdquo; In 1993, it was transformed into the   Kyrgyz State National University and later, in 2002, it received the status of   &ldquo;National&rdquo; and was renamed as the Kyrgyz National University named   after J. Balasagyn. </p> <h3>Milestones</h3> <ul>   <li>     Since October 20, 1989 KNU has been a member of Eurasian Association of     Universities.   </li>   <li>     On September 16, 2011 the Rector of KNU signed the Great Charter of     Universities in Bologna.   </li>   <li>     On June 30, 2012 KNU became a member of the Association of Asian     Universities.   </li>   <li>     Since November 8, 2013 KNU has been a member of the International Consortium     of Rectors and Presidents of Universities and Higher Education Institutions     on the basis of the International Network of Universities and Higher     Education Institutions.   </li>   <li>     Since November 22, 2013 KNU named after. J. Balasagyna is a member of the     Association of Universities of Turkic Speaking Countries.   </li>   <li>     In 2014, KNU joined the Association of Higher Educational Institutions of     the Kyrgyz Republic   </li>   <li>     In 2019 signing of a bilateral agreement between KNU and LNCT Group/LN     Medical College Bhopal for the medical faculty, which includes an exchange     programme for Indian and Kyrgyz students.   </li>   <li>     In 2023 The President of the Kyrgyz Republic granted special status for     Kyrgyz National University   </li> </ul>  <h3>International Joint Projects</h3>  <p>   The university has signed agreements with various international projects and   organizations, such as ISTC, INTAS, IREKS, and TEMPUS, to promote educational   and scientific cooperation These agreements facilitate collaboration with over   50 renowned foreign universities, centers, and international programs in   Europe, the United States, and Canada. </p> <p>   Additionally, the university actively participates in university associations   of developed countries, including Eurasian and Lingua-UNI. It is also a member   of the Consortium of CIS universities network, the Eurasian Association of   Universities, and the Universities of the Shanghai Cooperation Organization.   As a result, graduates of KNU have the opportunity to pursue studies abroad   through the mentioned projects and initiatives. </p>  <h3>A Premier Destination for Medical Education</h3>  <p>   Experience our distinguished MBBS program, designed to equip students with the   knowledge and skills required for a successful medical career. </p>  <h3>Specialized&nbsp;<strong>NEXT</strong>&nbsp;Preparation Classes</h3>  <p>   At Kyrgyz National University, we believe in providing our students with the   best opportunities for a successful future. Recognizing the significance of   the NEXT exam for both foreign and Indian medical graduates, our Faculty of   Medicine, in partnership with LNMC, offers specialized on-campus classes for   NEXT preparation. These classes are designed to ensure that our medical   graduates are fully prepared and equipped to excel in this mandatory exam. </p> <p>   Our commitment goes beyond delivering medical education; we strive to support   our students at every step of their journey towards a successful career. The   NEXT class at KNULNMC is a testament to our dedication to our students&rsquo;   success. </p>  <h3>Advance Medical Pedagogy</h3>  <p>(Foreign Medical Graduate Licentiate)</p>  <p>   The LNCT Group of Bhopal, India, launched the Indo-Kyrgyz initiative to make   medical education affordable for Indian students. Through an MOU with Kyrgyz   National University, LN Medical College Bishkek was established within the KNU   infrastructure, bringing refined Indianized medical education, modern   technology, and healthcare infrastructure to Kyrgyzstan. LNMC Bishkek, the   first-ever Indian medical college in a foreign land, offers global medical   education with state-of-the-art facilities and experienced faculty. </p> <p>   Recognized by prestigious international organizations, it provides world-class   yet economical education for aspiring medical professionals, collaborating   with Kyrgyz National University to offer a global perspective. </p>  <h3>Clinical Rotation</h3>  <p>   Kyrgyz National University and our Medical faculty partner LNCT groups and LN   Medical College Bhopal, recognizes the significance of practical clinical   exposure and hands-on experience for students. Our Clinical Rotation Program   provides a unique opportunity for students to gain valuable clinical   experience in Indian hospitals and familiarize themselves with the standard   medical approach for prevalent indigenous diseases. </p> <p>   This program is meticulously designed to offer comprehensive training,   preparing our students to tackle medical challenges worldwide.We take immense   pride in offering this program as one of our key differentiators that sets us   apart from other medical institutions. </p>  <h3>Separate Campus</h3>  <p>(Foreign Medical Graduate Licentiate)</p>  <p>   Kyrgyz National University and our medical faculty partner LNCT Groups and   LNMC, understands the challenges faced by Indian students studying in a   foreign country. To address this, the university has established a dedicated   campus exclusively for Indian students. </p> <p>   This separate campus provides Indian students with their own classes, hostels,   libraries, and other facilities to ensure their comfort and convenience. By   creating a sense of community and connection to their homeland, this   arrangement fosters a stress-free environment and ultimately enhances the   academic performance of the students. </p>  <h3>English Curriculum</h3>  <p>   Kyrgyz National University, is a unilingual university with English as the   medium of instruction for medical education. Our comprehensive curriculum is   delivered entirely in English, ensuring a seamless academic experience. We   offer scholarships based on merit, financial need, athletics, and career   goals, promoting equal access to quality education. </p> <p>   Our campus boasts modern infrastructure, including spacious classrooms with   advanced technology, a well-stocked library, and sports facilities. At LNMC,   we prioritize providing a conducive learning environment for our   students&rsquo; development. </p>  <h3>Scholarship</h3>  <p>(Foreign Medical Graduate Licentiate)</p>  <p>   Kyrgyz National University, promotes equality and access to quality education   by offering various scholarships to deserving students. These scholarships aim   to support bright students who may not have the financial means to afford   their education. Different categories and eligibility criteria are available   for these scholarships. </p>  <ul>   <li>Merit-based scholarship</li>   <li>Need-based Scholarship</li>   <li>Athletic Scholarship</li>   <li>Career-based Scholarship</li> </ul>', 'KYRGYZ NATIONAL MEDICAL UNIVERSITY – Universities | MBBS | Colleges', 'Kyrgyz National Medical University provides world-class education in MBBS and Medical studies. Visit our campus to know more.'),
(2, 'ADAM UNIVERSITY SCHOOL OF MEDICINE', 1, '', 1, '<p>   The School of Medicine is the structural division of Adam university,   officially approved by the Ministry of Health and Ministry of Education and   Science of Kyrgyz Republic with the license&nbsp;<a     href=\"https://fm.adam.kg/accreditation/legislative-documents/\"     rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"     >LD170001314</a   >. </p> <p>   After graduation students can pursue a wide variety of careers   internationally. Students have an opportunity to continue their education in   any higher field in their home country or abroad and become doctor,   specialists, doctoral level or have a job requiring a medical degree. </p> <h2>Faculty of Medicine</h2> <p>   Adam university is a higher educational institute, established in 1994 in   Bishkek city the capital of Kyrgyz Republic to provide education, research and   training on Business, Finance, Economics, Tourism and medicine for the   transition economies of the central Asia. The mission is to promote a society   in the development of market and social institutions through the training of   competent personnel in different fields. </p> <p>   The medical school is the structural division of Adam university officially   approved by the Ministry of Health and Ministry of education of Kyrgyz   Republic with the license No. LD170001314. for promotion of high quality   medical education and providing health diagnostic services and treatment to   local population </p> <p>   The medicine program of Adam university is taught in English language and the   duration of course is 5 years. Well-equipped training rooms with modern   computers and medical training simulators and analyzers are placed at   university campuses. For organization of education process, our teachers use   modern software like &ldquo;Simformer&rdquo;, &rdquo;Webex&rdquo; and   &ldquo;Virtumed&rdquo; which are given possibilities to our students create   their individual work in effective way. The medicine program has a curriculum   where science and medical disciplines are highly integrated to ensure an   optimum learning experience. </p> <p>   Training is conducted in line up with European Educational Standard which   enables students to migrate to European and other universities during the   study or after completion of their degree. </p> <p>   After graduation students can pursue a wide variety of careers   internationally. Students have an opportunity to continue their education in   any higher field in their home country or abroad and become doctor,   specialists, doctoral level or have a job requiring a medical degree. </p> <h3>Departments</h3> <p>   There are 45 study Departments in medical study and curriculum is very rich in   knowledge more enough as a student needs to be become a qualified doctor. </p> <h3>Duration of Courses</h3> <p>5 Years MBBS/MD in english medium.</p> <p>   <a     href=\"https://adam.edu.kg/media/attach/2021/04/03/Academic_calendar_GM_2020-2021.pdf\"     rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"     >Academic calendar</a   > </p> <h3>Teaching Staff</h3> <p>   Our teachers are wholly committed to imparting education and students have the   benefit of their expertise and knowledge every single day,right through the   year.A large number of our teachers have terminal qualifications and graduated   from Russia,Europe,Uk and America.Every years teachers are also invited from   European countries and from countries like India,Pakistan,Bangladesh,Nepal on   agreement basis to deliver lectures for one or 2 months period.This enhance   the knowledge of students that make them easy to pass their medical council   exams in their home countries after graduation. </p> <p>   Our teaching staff are highly professional,among them there are professor   doctors,doctors of medical science,candidates of medical science,doctors of   biological science and pedagogical science who have significant experience on   their areas.All our teachers are fluent in English Language. </p> <p>   In National Hospital there are 160 number of staff and among them there are 6   professor doctors,36 candidates of medical science and 118 doctor of science   including 41 with highest qualification category. </p> <p>   In Chui Hospital there are 30 doctors and more than 10 candidates and doctors   of science. Our university is in step with times.we conduct online lectures   with participation of leading specialists in various fields of medicine from   universities in moscow,europe,pakistan,bangladesh,india and some other   countries. For September 2018 is scheduled to lecture by Savostikova Marina   Vladimirovna. This is a good opportunity for professionals to increase their   knowledge, and for students to learn the basics of Biological science and   microscopic anatomy.&nbsp; </p> <p>   Marina Vladimirovna is Candidate of medical Sciences and head of the   laboratory of clinical Cytology of the fsbu&rdquo;. N. N. Blokhin&rdquo; the   Ministry of health. Vice-President of the Association of Oncopathologies. She   is author of 143 scientific papers, 8 of them abroad, 8 textbooks for   physicians, 37 presentations at scientific conferences. She is author of the   &ldquo;Atlas of cytologic and immunocytochemical diagnosis of tumors&rdquo;   2010 Leading specialist in the field of standard and fluorescent   immunocytochemistry, liquid-based Cytology and cell-block techniques. </p> <p>   Above all,we have great staff-student relations as we understand that the care   and support of our students is our first priority. </p>', 'Best MBBS colleges in Kyrgyzstan | ADAM UNIVERSITY SCHOOL OF MEDICINE', 'Among leading MBBS colleges in Kyrgyzstan, Adam  University School of Medicine Kyrgyzstan has a world-class campus. It is among the top Schools of Medicine in Kyrgyzstan.'),
(3, 'AVICENNA INTERNATIONAL UNIVERSITY', 1, '', 1, '<p>A beautiful arranged modern campus with well-equipped academic and hospital buildings is the beauty of the area. It is situated at Road 8, Dhanmondi, Dhaka 1205, at the heart of the capital market. It has two lecture room and in number 1 altogether&nbsp;200 students can sit together with multimedia presentation facilities. Also a modern library with 5000 recent medical text books on different disciplines and internet facilities, computer room were available for students and academic staff of the college.&nbsp;AKMMC main hospital building accommodates cabins, general wards, consultant chambers, operation theater, ICU, reception, modern diagnostic lab and hospital office. 2 lecture room one large with 300 seat capacity and one small with full air conditioned, multimedia presentation facilities, are located in 5th&amp; 6th floor of Block A. Fully air conditioned, modern, well decorated and equipped floor space measuring 20,500 square feet at 4th&amp; 5th floor of capital market is accommodating <strong>Departments of Anatomy, Physiology, Biochemistry, Pathology, Pharmacology, Forensic Medicine, Microbiology, Community Medicine</strong> with tutorial and practical classes, museum and sitting arrangement of all academic staff of the departments mentioned. 1 lecture room with central air-conditioning, multimedia presentation and accommodations of 150 students is located in 5th floor of capital market Fulltime OPD facilities covering all disciplines <strong>Medicine, Surgery Pediatrics, Gyane &amp; Obstetrics: Skin VD, ENT Eye, Psychiatry, Orthopedics and Oncology</strong> are available at OPD located in 2nd &amp; 3rd floor of first main building (A) of the college.</p>                      <p>Anwer Khan Modern Nursing college is a unit under AKMMC is located in 3rd floor of ARA plaza just opposite to our main building A covering 4000 sft accommodating 3 class room, 5 lecture room, 3 faculty room, 10 office assistant, 1 MLSS. Total no of students admitted up to this session is 120 (Diploma 83,33 BSc Nursing, Post basic Nursing 14.)</p>                      <p><strong>Available Facilities </strong></p>                      <ul>                         <li>Five lecture halls with state of the art audiovisual facilities.</li>                         <li>Adequate spacious class rooms for all the departments.</li>                         <li>Laboratories for different departments.</li>                         <li>Central computerized library with the internet facility</li>                         <li>Office space for college administration and management.</li>                         <li>All facilities mentioned above are fully air-conditioned.</li>                         <li>Prayer facilities for the students &amp; staff.</li>                         <li>Cafeteria facilities for the students &amp; staff.</li>                     </ul>                      <p><strong>Proposed facilities</strong></p>                      <ul>                         <li>Auditorium.</li>                         <li>Healthcare facilities with gymnasium.</li>                         <li>Own hall or residence for students.</li>                         <li>Other facilities as would be necessary.</li>                         <li>Own transport facility.</li>                     </ul>                     <p>Anwer Khan Modern Medical College offers 5 years MBBS course approved by BM &amp; DC leading to an MBBS degree under the University of Dhaka.</p>                      <p>The college has been permitted to operate by the Ministry of Health &amp; Family Welfare, Government&nbsp;of the Peoples&nbsp;Republic of Bangladesh and affiliated with the University of Dhaka.</p>                      <h3><strong>Eligibility Criteria for international students</strong></h3>                      <p><strong>The candidate needs to produce all valid documents proving the eligibility to seek admission in the Anwer Khan Modern Medical College:</strong></p>                      <ul>                         <li>The student must have at least 17 years of age to apply for MBBS course education.</li>                         <li>The students must have to secure at least 50% marks in physics, chemistry, and biology subjects.</li>                         <li>Open category students must secure 45% scores in PCB subjects.</li>                         <li>ST/SC/OBC category students must secure an aggregate of 50% scores in PCB subjects.</li>                         <li>The students have to qualify for a NEET entrance examination for MBBS admission.</li>                     </ul>                      <p>&nbsp;</p>                      <p>&nbsp;</p>                      <p><strong>HOW &amp; WHEN TO APPLY</strong></p>                      <p>&nbsp;</p>                      <ul>                         <li>Local students should apply according to the instruction of Director General of Health Services (DGHS) after the result of medical admission test.</li>                         <li>Foreign students should apply in the month of September – December.</li>                         <li>Those interested to apply for admission should at first get their S.S.C/O level, H.S.C/A level or equivalent certificates &amp; mark sheets attested by the Ministry of Education as well as Ministry of Foreign Affairs of their own country.</li>                         <li>After that they should apply through the Embassy of Bangladesh in their country providing above mentioned attested documents.</li>                         <li>The Office of Director General of Health Services (DGHS), Dhaka, Bangladesh will then issue Equivalence Certificate which can be collected either through the Bangladesh Mission in their country or directly from the Office of DGHS.</li>                     </ul>                      <p><strong>DOCUMENTS TO BE SUBMITTED</strong></p>                      <ul>                         <li>For admission into 1st year MBBS course all students need to apply in prescribed form along with the following documents:</li>                         <li>Attested photocopy of SSC &amp; HSC/ Equivalent Exam Certificate/ Testimonial.</li>                         <li>Attested photocopy of SSC &amp; HSC/ Equivalent Exam Mark Sheets/ Academic Transcript.</li>                         <li>Attested photocopy of Equivalence Certificate issued by DGHS, Dhaka, Bangladesh (for students with \"O\" &amp; \"A\" level).</li>                         <li>Three copies of recent passport size Color Photographs.</li>                         <li>Photocopy of Passport/ National ID Card.</li>                         <li>At the time of admission all original documents will be retained by the college until completion of the course.</li>                         <li>1st year MBBS class usually starts from first week of January or as decided by the Government each year.</li>                     </ul>                      <p><strong>SCOPE FOR MCI, NMC</strong></p>                      <ul>                         <li>After obtaining MBBS Degree from Bangladesh, students from India are required to appear in FMGE test, conducted by Medical Council of India.</li>                     </ul>                      <p>MBBS degree obtained from EMC is recognized by NMC &amp; other SAARC countries.</p>                     <h3><strong>Class Rooms</strong></h3>                      <p>There are 5 large fully air conditioned class rooms. In addition, there are departmental tutorial rooms attached with the respective departments. The Anatomy Dissection Hall is fully air conditioned.</p>                      <p>The laboratories of various departments like Pathology, Biochemistry, etc are well equipped with instruments.</p>                      <h3><strong>Audiovisual Equipment</strong></h3>                      <p>Each class is provided with overhead projector, slide projector and microphone system. In addition, multimedia projectors and computers are also available for teaching.</p>                      <p>There are 5 large fully air conditioned class rooms. In addition, there are departmental tutorial rooms attached with the respective departments. The Anatomy Dissection Hall is fully air conditioned. The laboratories of various departments like Pathology, Biochemistry, etc are well equipped with instruments.</p>                      <h3><strong>Library</strong></h3>                      <p>The College has a modern fully air-conditioned library with Internet facilities. The library has a collection of over 1565 books including expensive latest journals. It subscribes 16 international medical journals on an annual basis.</p>                      <p>The library has accommodation for seating 100 students and 15 teachers at any given time. The Medical Education Unit (MEU) is attached to the library.</p>                      <p>MEU has computers for use by students and faculty members. Fax, Internet, and E-mail facilities are freely available and are widely used.</p>                      <h3><strong>Anwer Khan Modern Medical College Hospital</strong></h3>                      <p>Anwer Khan Modern Medical College Hospital is a 450 bed, state of the art hospital located in Dhanmondi Dhaka. It offers comprehensive healthcare services.</p>                      <p>Equipped with the most advanced medical technology, and staff by a team of highly skill healthcare professionals AKMMCH is committed to providing high-quality care in a friendly hospital environment.</p>                      <p>&nbsp;</p>                      <p><em><strong>Address:&nbsp;</strong></em></p>                      <table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">                         <tbody>                             <tr>                                 <td>                                     <p><br>                                         <em><strong>House No.17,Road No.8 Dhanmondi,Dhaka</strong></em>.                                     </p>                                 </td>                             </tr>                         </tbody>                     </table>                     <h3><strong>For International Students</strong></h3>                      <p><strong>MODE OF PAYMENT</strong></p>                      <p>1) During Admission Payment (1st Installment) = US$ 26,000.00</p>                      <p>2) 2nd Installment (July 2022)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; = US$ 2,000.00</p>                      <p>3) 3rd Installment (January 2023) = US$ 5,000.00</p>                      <p>4) 4th Installment (January 2024) = US$ 5,000.00</p>                      <p>5) 5th Installment (January 2025) = US$ 5,000.00</p>                      <p>6) 6th Installment (January 2026) = US$ 1,000.00</p>                      <p>---------------------------------------------------------------------------</p>                      <p>Grand Total&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;=&nbsp;US$ 44,000.00 (US$ Forty Four Thousand)</p>                      <p>7) Hostel Fee (Non-A/C) = Including Course Fee.</p>                      <p>8) Hostel Security = BDT. 25,000 (US$ 300) onetime payment as non-refundable (After arrival at Bangladesh).</p>                      <p>9) Clinical Placement Fee = BDT. 50,000 (US$ 600, On July 2021).</p>                      <p>10) Utility Bill = BDT. 2,000 (Two Thousand Taka) per month.</p>                      <p>11) Food Cost = Self at actual cost.</p>                      <p>&nbsp;</p>                      <p><strong>Condition of Payment:</strong></p>                      <p>Interested students need to confirm their eligibility for admitting MBBS course in Bangladesh by sending all academic documents. After that, students need to pay US$ 10,000 to college bank account as advance tuition fee for booking International Students Seats in “Anwer Khan Modern Medical College”. This amount will be adjusted from your first installment of admission fee (Admission Payment). A letter of confirmed admission will be issued when the first installment tuition fee received by the college.</p>                      <p>&nbsp;</p>                      <p><strong>Bank Details</strong></p>                      <p>You have to pay fee by TT/ Swift Transfer to<strong> “Anwer Khan Modern Medical College” Bank Account Number:</strong> <strong>0000233012814, SWIFT CODE</strong>: <strong>SDBL BDDH102 maintained with Standard Bank Limited, </strong>Principle Branch, Metropolitan Chamber Building (Mezzanine Floor), 122-124 Motijheel C/A, Dhaka-1000, Bangladesh.</p>                      <p>&nbsp;</p>                      <p><strong>Students need to submit the following papers for processing of admission:</strong></p>                      <ul>                         <li>Eligibility certificate from Medical Council.</li>                         <li>Certified copy (English Translated) of the marks/grade sheet of the qualifying examination.</li>                         <li>Certified copy of the grade equivalence to marks by Boards/School.</li>                         <li>Copy of passport.</li>                         <li>Proof of NRI status of the student/parents/sponsor.</li>                         <li>Passport size photographs (recent).</li>                         <li>Nationality Certificate.</li>                         <li>Details resume with contact details of students &amp; parents (Mobile, E-mail &amp; Residential Address).</li>                     </ul>', 'AVICENNA INTERNATIONAL UNIVERSITY – Universities | MBBS | Colleges', 'Avicenna International University provides world-class education in MBBS and Medical studies. Visit our campus to know more.'),
