edical staff. 32,400 Emergencies Per Year Sylhet Women\'s Medical College is a mid-sized community teaching hospital presently it has 625 beds throughout its three 9 story buildings. Each year we care for approximately 15,000 inpatients, treat more than 160,000 people in our outpatient medical clinics and handle more than 58,000 Emergency Care visits Workforce of 600 Sylhet Women\'s Medical College &amp; Hospital is the one of the largest employers in Sylhet Division with over 600 employees, including full-time, part-time and per diem individuals Helping Area Residents Stay Healthy Community health education is one of our strengths at Sylhet Women\'s Medical College &amp; Hospital. We provide low-cost health screenings for mature adults.</p>                         <p><strong>Course Offered </strong></p>                          <p>MBBS 5years and Internship 1year</p>                          <p><strong>Foreign student’s admission requirements</strong></p>                          <p>Foreign students need to apply according to the rules &amp; regulations of their respective countries through their Embassies.</p>                          <p>Students need to collect the equivalence certificate of S.S.S / ‘O’ Level and H.S.C / ‘A’ Level from the Director-General of Health Services.</p>                         <p><strong>College Library </strong></p>                          <p>Holy Land Private Limited and Sylhet Health and Education Services Limited joined together in 2005 for a noble cause in medical education and health care. Together they formed Holy Sylhet Holding Limited. In 2007, Holy Sylhet Holding Limited (HSHL) commenced the college and hospital with the permission of the Government of Bangladesh and after completing all the necessary formalities with the respective Ministries, Departments, Medical Associations and University.HSHL also has plans to establish a Dental College and 4-year Nursing College on its 3-Acre property in the heart of Sylhet City.</p>   