(14, 'IMMANUEL KANT BALTIC FEDERAL UNIVERSITY', 1, 'Immanuel-Kant-Baltic-Federal-University.png', 3, '<h2>Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University</h2>  <p>   Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University&nbsp;was founded in 1967 expanding on   the already existing Kaliningrad State Pedagogical University that had been   founded in 1947. The history of the University began with the establishment of   the State Pedagogical Institute in Kaliningrad. IKBFU is a leading university   of the Kaliningrad region and one of the ten federal universities of the   Russian Federation. </p> <p>   Conveniently located in the heart of Europe,&nbsp;Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal   University&nbsp;attracts students and researchers from around the world. Today   citizens from 40 countries of the world &ndash; from Europe, Latin America,   Asia and Africa &ndash; study at different levels and conduct research at the   University. </p> <p>   Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University&nbsp;carefully keeps the academic   traditions of its predecessor &ndash; the &lsquo;Albertina&rsquo; University   of K&ouml;nigsberg and introduces the newest technologies of Russian classical   education. </p>  <h3>Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University Overview</h3>  <table>   <tbody>     <tr>       <td><strong>Year of Establishment</strong></td>       <td>1947</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>Type of University</strong></td>       <td>Government</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>Duration of MBBS</strong></td>       <td>5.8 years</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>Recognitions</strong></td>       <td>NMC (erstwhile MCI), FAIMER, WDOMS, ECFMG</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>Intake period</strong></td>       <td>September</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>Medium of teaching</strong></td>       <td>English</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>NEET Requirement</strong></td>       <td>Yes</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>Eligibility Exam (IELTS/TOEFL)</strong></td>       <td>No</td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table>  <h3>Recognitions of Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University</h3>  <p>Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University is recognized by:</p> <ol>   <li>     <ol>       <li>National Medical Commission (erstwhile Medical Council of India);</li>       <li>Ministry of Science and Higher Education, Russia (MSHE);</li>       <li>World Directory of Medical Schools (WDOMS);</li>       <li>Education Commission for Foreign Medical Graduates (ECFMG);</li>       <li>         Foundation for Advancement of International Medical Education and         Research (FAIMER).       </li>     </ol>   </li> </ol>  <h3>Faculties of Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University</h3>  <p>There are 4 faculties in Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University:</p> <ol>   <li>     <ol>       <li>Faculty of Medicine</li>       <li>Faculty of Surgical Disciplines</li>       <li>Faculty of Obstetrics &amp; Gynecology</li>       <li>Faculty of Therapy</li>     </ol>   </li> </ol>  <h3>Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University Fees Structure</h3>  <table>   <tbody>     <tr>       <td><strong>Fees Structure</strong></td>       <td><strong>1st Year</strong></td>       <td><strong>2nd Year</strong></td>       <td><strong>3rd Year</strong></td>       <td><strong>4th Year</strong></td>       <td><strong>5th Year</strong></td>       <td><strong>6th Year</strong></td>       <td><strong>Total Course Package</strong></td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>Tuition Fee</strong></td>       <td>$ 4,000</td>       <td>$ 4,000</td>       <td>$ 4,000</td>       <td>$ 4,000</td>       <td>$ 4,000</td>       <td>$ 4,000</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>Hostel Fee</strong></td>       <td>$ 500</td>       <td>$ 500</td>       <td>$ 500</td>       <td>$ 500</td>       <td>$ 500</td>       <td>$ 500</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>Total Fees in USD</strong></td>       <td>$ 4,500</td>       <td>$ 4,500</td>       <td>$ 4,500</td>       <td>$ 4,500</td>       <td>$ 4,500</td>       <td>$ 4,500</td>       <td>$ 27,000</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>Total Fees in Rs</strong></td>       <td>₹ 3,37,500</td>       <td>₹ 3,37,500</td>       <td>₹ 3,37,500</td>       <td>₹ 3,37,500</td>       <td>₹ 3,37,500</td>       <td>₹ 3,37,500</td>       <td>₹ 20,25,000</td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table>  <p>   *<strong     ><em       >Calculations are as per the current market value of Indian Rupee against       US Dollar (1 USD = INR 75)</em     ></strong   > </p>  <p><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;</p> <ul>   <li>     The above-mentioned fee structure is the final amount to be paid by the     student to Rus Education.   </li>   <li>     This fee package includes Tuition fee, Hostel accommodation fee, medical     insurance, remuneration to the centre, MCI coaching for the complete     duration of the course, airport transfer to the university, a phone call to     parents on arrival in the university, study material in English Language,     documentation of the student in the university, free translator to     facilitate, and other services.   </li> </ul>  <h3>   Eligibility Criteria for Admission in Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University </h3>  <p>   Any Indian student applying to Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University to   pursue MBBS in Russia must fulfill the following: </p> <ul>   <li>     <strong>Age requirement:&nbsp;</strong>The applicant should be 17 years of     age as on 31st December in the admission year.   </li>   <li>     <strong>Academic requirements:&nbsp;</strong>The applicant must have passed     12th standard with at least 50% score in Physics, Chemistry, and Biology and     English as a compulsory subject.   </li>   <li>     <strong>NEET requirements:&nbsp;</strong>Passed NEET exam (50th percentile     for general/EWS category and 40th percentile for unreserved category)   </li> </ul>  <h3>Admission Process</h3>  <p>   The process for MBBS admission in Russia in Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal   University is as follows: </p> <ol>   <li>Fill the online application form with your required details.</li>   <li>     &nbsp;Submit your educational and other documents with the application form.   </li>   <li>     The university will send an admission/invitation letter confirming your     admission in the university.   </li>   <li>Apply for the student visa to the Russian Embassy in India.</li>   <li>Make travel arrangements to fly to Russia for MBBS studies.</li> </ol>  <h3>Documents Required</h3>  <p>   The admission process for&nbsp;<a     href=\"https://www.ruseducation.in/mbbs-in-russia/\"     rel=\"nofollow\"     >MBBS course</a   >&nbsp;in Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University requires the submission of   the following documents: </p> <ol>   <li>Pass certificates and mark sheet of class 10th and 12th.</li>   <li>HIV negative report</li>   <li>Valid passport</li>   <li>Passport size photos</li>   <li>NEET scorecard</li>   <li>Transfer and migration certificate</li> </ol>  <h3>Why Study MBBS at Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University</h3>  <ul>   <li>Affordable fee structure for MBBS in Russia</li>   <li>Hassle-free admission procedure</li>   <li>Hostel facility available for international students</li>   <li>The lessons are taught in English and Russian.</li>   <li>Well-structured and advanced infrastructure</li>   <li>     Globally accepted medical degree to practice medicine anywhere in the world.   </li>   <li>     Advanced laboratories and classrooms for better theoretical and practical     exposure   </li>   <li>Clinical training at top hospitals and clinics.</li> </ul>  <h3>Student Life at Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University</h3>  <ul>   <li>     Organizing&nbsp;students&rsquo; extracurricular activities for their     holistic development.   </li>   <li>     Students organize various celebrations, festivals, excursions, and art     competitions all year long.   </li>   <li>     Students can enjoy the best sports facilities equipped for workouts and     competitions.   </li>   <li>     Sports activities in the university include basketball, volleyball,     badminton, table tennis, football, futsal, rugby, swimming, track and field     athletics, yoga, aerobics, athletics, hand-to-hand combat, self-defense,     rowing, Zumba, cheerleading, and others.   </li>   <li>     The University&rsquo;s excellent sports facilities include a swimming pool,     a stadium with running tracks and an artificial football pitch, an obstacle     course, a fitness suite, an aerobics studio, and several sports halls and     gyms.   </li>   <li>     Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University&rsquo;s Art Center offers freedom of     expression and opportunity for creativity to all students.   </li>   <li>There is&nbsp;24&times;7 wifi connectivity in the campus area.</li>   <li>     There are 7 dormitories within walking distance from the university campus.   </li>   <li>     There are 27 Research laboratories at Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal     University campus for the development of practical skills of the students.   </li>   <li>     Students have free access to several e-data bases like Cambridge Journals     Digital Archive Complete Collection, IOP Historic Archive, Oxford Online     Reference, etc.   </li> </ul>  <h3>City at a Glance</h3>  <ul>   <li>     Kaliningrad city is located on the Baltic Sea coast and belonged to Germany     for seven centuries.&nbsp;   </li>   <li>     95% of the population of Kaliningrad city speak Russian and understand the     English language.   </li>   <li>Kaliningrad is renowned for its amber production.</li>   <li>     Kaliningrad is&nbsp;home to the headquarters of the Baltic Fleet of the     Russian Navy.   </li>   <li>     K&ouml;nigsberg (now&nbsp;Kaliningrad)&nbsp;was the birthplace and home of     one of the world&rsquo;s greatest philosophers, Immanuel Kant.   </li> </ul>', 'IMMANUEL KANT BALTIC FEDERAL UNIVERSITY | IMC Consultancy', 'Immanuel Kant Baltic Federal University provides world-class education in MBBS and Medical studies. Visit our campus to know more.'),
(15, 'KEMEROVO STATE UNIVERSITY', 1, 'KEMEROVO-STATE-UNIVERSITY-russia.png', 3, '<p>   Kemerovo State Medical University is a public research university located in   the city of Kemerovo, Russia. It&rsquo;s one of the oldest universities in   Russia. Kemerovo State Medical University is always markable for its good   quality education with a pocket-friendly fee structure and the situated area   of the university is very beneficial because there you get everything   according to our comfort and convenience, the university taught more than 3500   students of medicine. </p> <p>   Kemerovo State Medical University offers a variety of undergraduate and   graduate programs in various fields, including medicine. The Faculty of   Medicine at Kemerovo State Medical University offers a 6-year MBBS program   (Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery) that is taught entirely in   English. The program is developed to provide students with a complete   education in medical science, as well as applicable training in hospitals and   clinics.&nbsp; </p> <p>   Studying MBBS at Kemerovo State Medical University offers several benefits for   international students who hope to study MBBS abroad. The university also has   a highly skilled faculty, state-of-the-art facilities, and a vibrant student   community. Students have many locations and advantages for touring in their   holidays and apart from education Russia is also a good place for traveling   for touring, Russia has a lower crime rate for students there lots of places   are available and the weather is amazing to enjoy the days. </p> <h2>Why Choose the Kemerovo State Medical University?</h2> <p>   Kemerovo State Medical University has a reputation for academic excellence and   is accredited by the Russian Federation\'s Ministry of Education and Science.   Studying at Kemerovo State Medical University is affordable compared to other   countries, and living expenditures in Russia are lower than in many European   countries. K