(16, 'ORENBURG STATE MEDICAL UNIVERSITY', 1, 'Orenburg-State-Medical-University-RUSSIA.png', 3, '<p>   Orenburg State Medical University is one of the top-ranked universities in   Russia. More than 700 Indian Students are already studying at Orenburg State   Medical University. </p> <p>   Established in 1944, Orenburg State Medical University is a non-profit public   higher education institution located in the medium-sized city of Orenburg   (population range of 500,000-1,000,000 inhabitants), Orenburg Oblast. Orenburg   State Medical University is officially accredited and recognized by the   Ministry of Health of the Russian Federation. </p> <p>   Nowadays activity of the Orenburg State Medical University satisfies all   modern standards and requirements presented to medical School. </p> <p>   Specialists in the sphere of medicine graduated from the University for many   years. Graduates of the Orenburg Medical University work in state and private   medical and preventive institutions, take leading positions in state   administrative structures, solve primary issues on the development of modern   medicine. </p> <p>   Orenburg State Medical University (OrSMA) is a (uniRank enrollment range:   3,000-3,999 students) coeducational higher education institution. </p> <p>   Orenburg State Medical University (OrSMA) offers courses and programs leading   to officially recognized higher education degrees such as bachelor&rsquo;s   degrees, master&rsquo;s degrees, doctorate degrees in several areas of study.   Currently, there are eight faculties: Medicine, Pediatric, Stomatology   (Dentistry), Pharmacy, Clinical Psychology, Nursing, Public Health. </p> <h3>Hospitals</h3> <p>   There are over 18 clinical bases aimed at training of students in Orenburg:<br />1.   Municipal city clinical hospital number 1<br />2. Municipal city clinical   hospital named after Pirogov N.I.<br />3. Orenburg regional clinical hospital   no. 1.<br />4. Municipal city clinical hospital number 2.<br />5. Railway   clinical hospital of Orenburg station.<br />6. Polyclinic of the municipal   city clinical hospital number 5<br />7. Orenburg regional clinical hospital no   2 </p> <h3>ORENBURG STATE MEDICAL UNIVERSITY &ndash; FACULTIES</h3> <ul>   <li>Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology</li>   <li>Department of Human Anatomy</li>   <li>Department of Hospital Therapies</li>   <li>Hospital Surgery Department, Urology</li>   <li>Department of Children&rsquo;s Diseases</li>   <li>The Department of outpatient therapy</li>   <li>Department of General Surgery</li>   <li>The Department of Surgery and Clinical Anatomy&nbsp;</li>   <li>Department of Internal Medicine Propaedeutics</li>   <li>Department of Traumatology and Orthopedics</li>   <li>The Department of Therapy and Endocrinology</li>   <li>The Department of Surgery</li> </ul> <h5><strong>Dentistry faculties:</strong></h5> <ul>   <li>Department of Ophthalmology</li>   <li>Department of Biological Chemistry</li>   <li>Department of Pathological Physiology</li>   <li>Department of Dentistry and Maxillofacial Surgery</li>   <li>Dept. of Physiology</li>   <li>The Department of Physical Education</li>   <li>The Department of Surgery and Clinical Anatomy</li>   <li>Department of Dentistry</li> </ul> <h5><strong>Faculty of Pharmacy:</strong></h5> <ul>   <li>Department of Biology</li>   <li>Department of Biophysics and math</li>   <li>     Department of Management and Economics of Pharmacy, Pharmaceutical     Technology and Pharmacognosy   </li>   <li>Department of Chemistry and Pharmaceutical Chemistry</li> </ul> <h3>University Rankings:</h3> <p>   According to 4icu World University rankings, Orenburg State medical university   rank #5269 in World rankings and holds 184th rank in Russia. </p> <h3>   MBBS fees of Orenburg State Medical University &ndash; Fees Structure 2023 </h3>  <table>   <thead>     <tr>       <th>ORENBURG STATE MEDICAL UNIVERSITY, RUSSIA</th>       <th>TUITION FEE / YEAR</th>       <th>HOSTEL FEE / YEAR</th>       <th>FEES IN US DOLLARS</th>       <th>FEES IN INDIAN RUPEES</th>     </tr>   </thead>   <tbody>     <tr>       <td>1st Year Fees</td>       <td>5500 USD</td>       <td>500 USD</td>       <td>6000 USD</td>       <td>RS. 4,80,000 Rupees</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>2nd to 6th Year fees</td>       <td>5500 USD/ YR.</td>       <td>500 USD/ YR.</td>       <td>6000 USD/ YR.</td>       <td>RS.4,80,000/YR.</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Total Fees for 6-years MBBS</td>       <td>36,000 US Dollars = Rs. 28,80,000 ( Exchange rate 1 USD = 80 INR)</td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table>  <p>   <strong>Tuition Fees &ndash;</strong>&nbsp;Includes Study Materials, Library   Charge, Laboratory Charge &amp; Examination Fee.<br /><strong     >Hostel Fees &ndash;</strong   >&nbsp;Includes Accommodation, Bedding, Furniture, 24-hrs Electricity, 24-hrs   Gas in Separate Kitchen, 24-hrs Hot &amp;Cold water supply, and Centralized   Room heating system.<br /><strong>Food:</strong>&nbsp;Indian Mess is available   at Orenburg State Medical University for Indian students. Food is served two   times a day i.e. Lunch and Dinner. Food fulfills the balanced diet   requirements of a student. Vegetarian and Non-Vegetarian food is cooked and   served separately. </p> <h3>Admission Requirements 2023:</h3> <p>   Orenburg State Medical University has defined some eligibility standards for   admission in medical courses. Admissions are based on the past academic   records of applicants. International students are eligible for enrollment if: </p> <ul>   <li>The applicant has at least 50% marks in 10+2 in science subjects.</li>   <li>The candidate must be 17 years of age by December 31, 2020.</li>   <li>The applicant must qualify in NEET Exam to get admission.</li>   <li>     The applicant is not suffering from any contagious disease i.e.     tuberculosis, HIV AIDS, etc.   </li> </ul> <h3>Admission Procedure in six easy steps:</h3> <ol>   <li>Submit the Application form along with the required documents.</li>   <li>Pay Application Fees and get a confirmation letter.</li>   <li>Submit Passport, get Visa/Invitation Letter.</li>   <li>Get Visa and fly to Russia.</li>   <li>On arrival, pay University Fees.</li>   <li>Join your classes.</li> </ol> <h3>University Hostels:</h3> <p>   Orenburg State Medical University has 3 hostels. The third hostel is reserved   for Indian students. These hostels give a very homely feeling for the students   who came from different places. There is a sports club in the University which   was first inaugurated in the year 2013. Organizing and improving sports work   for students, the propaganda of a healthy lifestyle, and upgrading of   sportsmanship is the prime aim of the University. There are 12 sports leagues   in the club in which all the Indian students participate such as; aerobics,   swimming, basketball, volleyball, indoor soccer, track-and-field athletics,   table tennis, lifting, skiing, chess, etc. </p> <h3>Why study MBBS at Orenburg State Medical University?</h3> <ul>   <li>No entrance exams are required and no donations are to be paid.</li>   <li>Easy Admission procedure</li>   <li>High standards of medical education.</li>   <li>The cost of studying MBBS in Russia is comparatively low.</li>   <li>The medium of education in Russia in English.</li>   <li>     The MBBS degree from Orenburg State Medical University is recognized by all     the major organizations like the World Health Organization (WHO) and also by     the Medical Council of India (MCI). The Indian students who complete their     MBBS from Orenburg state medical university can work in India as well after     passing Foreign Medical Graduate Examination.   </li>   <li>Hostels with the best facilities.</li>   <li>     More than 700 Indian Students are already studying at Orenburg State Medical     University.   </li>   <li>     The students can choose between English and Russian medium of study at their     convenience.   </li> </ul> <h3>About Orenburg City</h3> <p>   <strong>Orenburg</strong>&nbsp;(formerly Chkalov) town, capital of Orenburg   region, As of 2012, 570.3 thousand folks board Orenburg, urban population   equals to 554.7 thousand folks, rural population is 15.6 thousand folks   (Orenburg is that the twenty-eighth most inhabited town in Russia. The town   lies on the stream Ural (Yaik) next to the Sakmara stream outlet. Orenburg has   settled 1400 km to the East of Moscow, it lies absolutely in Europe. The total   space of the town is 259 sq. km. </p> <p>   It is a significant rail junction wherever the Trans-Caspian RR, the Central   Asian RR, and therefore the Samara-Orenburg line meet. based in 1735 as a   defense, Orenburg resisted (1773-74) an encirclement by Pugachev. It became a   middle for Russian trade with the Republic of Kazakhstan and Central Asia. it   had been referred to as Chkalov from 1938 to 1957. </p> <p>   The climate in Orenburg is extremely continental. The summer is hot and dry:   the average temperature during the day is above 15 degrees for 5 months a   year; the winter is moderately cold, maximum snow cover is observed in   February (23 cm). In summer the temperature can raise up to 40 degrees C,   sometimes it falls down to 5 degrees C. In winter the weather varies from   light to heavy frost, there are sometimes light thaws or severe frosts up to   20 degrees below zero. </p> <p>   POSTAL CODE &ndash; 460000<br />DIALING CODE &ndash; +7 3532<br />TIME ZONE   &ndash; UTC+6:00<br />TEMPERATURE &ndash; MINIMUM &ndash; 10, MAXIMUM + 40 </p>', 'ORENBURG STATE MEDICAL UNIVERSITY | IMC Consultancy', 'Orenburg State Medical University is one of the top-ranked universities in Russia. More than 700 Indian Students are already studying at Orenburg State Medical University.'),
(17, 'NORTHERN STATE MEDICAL UNIVERSITY', 1, 'Northern-State-Medical-University-RUSSIA.png', 3, '<p>   The Northern State Medical University is a high-quality institution of medical   education in Russia. It is situated in northern part of Russia and it also   offers amalgamation of Russian and European education. The university was   established in the year 1932. The university comprises of approximately 1000   staff, researchers, academicians, and professors. There are 18 faculties and   around 5500 students study in this university. The university receives   applications from around 17 countries in one academic session. These are the   faculties of in this university: </p>  <ol>   <li>Faculty of General Medicine</li>   <li>Faculty of Paediatric</li>   <li>Faculty of Dental</li>   <li>International faculty of general practitioners</li>   <li>Faculty of Nursing</li>   <li>Faculty of Postgraduate Education</li>   <li>Faculty of Pharmaceutical</li> </ol>  <h4>Key Features of the University</h4>  <p>   <strong     ><u       >The key features of the Northern State Medical University are:</u     ></strong   > </p>  <ol>   <li>     The university has modern and well-equipped labs. There are computers,     projectors, and all the necessary medical requirements.   </li>   <li>     The university has much international collaboration and students are engaged     in practical training in those nations.   </li>   <li>     It is one of the best universities in Russia for medicine. A very strict     university with professional teachers.   </li>   <li>     The medical graduates from this university get work opportunities in     countries like the U.S.A, the U.K., Germany, and Japan, etc.   </li>   <li>     It is a nice university, the MBBS course is offered in English. The number     of students here is huge but the quality of education is excellent.   </li>   <li>The hostels are within the campus itself and offer great support.</li>   <li>It is a good medical university with international standards.</li> </ol>  <h4>Ranking of the Northern State Medical University</h4>  <p>   The university has a good spot on the world ranking as well as ranking in the   country institutions as well. Northern State Medical University has a ranking   of 133 in Russia. It showcases its excellent quality of education. The   university has a good number of expert faculties and researchers. </p>  <h4>Life of Students in Northern State Medical University</h4>  <ol>   <li>     The students&rsquo; life at the Northern State Medical University is very     vibrant and dynamic.   </li>   <li>The students&rsquo; union is quite popular amongst the students.</li>   <li>     There is a fixed nominal membership fee which every student is required to     pay.   </li>   <li>     Foreign students are also given memberships and can enjoy the events and the     activities organised by the union.   </li>   <li>     There are many clubs and youth activities where you can participate and     enjoy a good social life.   </li>   <li>     These youth clubs organise various activities related to theatre, sports,     touring and adventure, etc.   </li>   <li>Students love enjoying entertainment activities along with studies.</li> </ol>  <h3>Accreditation of University</h3>  <p>   <strong     ><u       >This university is accredited by ministry of health and education which       indicates the fact that this is one of the universities which has global       recognition of it\'s MBBS degree.</u     ></strong   > </p>  <h3>Duration of the MBBS Course</h3>  <ol>   <li>     The duration of MBBS degree in Russia is 6 years. The last year of the MBBS     degree is the internship and training period.   </li>   <li>     The duration of MBBS is same in most of the universities in Russia. You get     a good exposure to sound theoretical experience and practical knowledge in 6     years of medical education.   </li> </ol>  <h4>NMC Approved University</h4>  <p>   Most of the medical universities in the country are recognised by the National   Medical Commission. For the Indian students it is good to study medicine only   from the universities approved by NMC as it will keep the door open to   practice medicine in India after the successful completion of your MBBS course   abroad. The universities arrange free NMC coaching for students coming from   India to help them clear the NMC screening test easily for a bright career.   Students can enjoy free online NMC Coaching during their MBBS course duration. </p>  <h3>Documents Required</h3>  <p>   The admission process is simple and transparent. There are very few and basic   documents which are needed for the admission process. The important documents   are listed below: </p>  <ol>   <li>You need to have the class 10 and class 12 marks sheets</li>   <li>     A migration certificate is required from the concerned institution/ board   </li>   <li>Passport size photographs, as required for the documents</li>   <li>     Aspirants also need medical insurance and medical certificate. The medical     certificate should specify that you don&rsquo;t suffer from any viral     diseases.   </li>   <li>Candidate should have a valid NEET scorecard</li> </ol>  <h4>Eligibility</h4>  <p>   The best aspect of admission in a medical university in Russia is that the   eligibility rules are simple. The following are the necessary requirements for   admission in medical degree in Northern State Medical University: </p>  <ol>   <li>The candidate must have attained 17 years of age</li>   <li>     A minimum of 50 percent marks are required in Chemistry, Biology, and     Physics   </li>   <li>     As mandated by the National Medical Commission, the candidate should have a     valid NEET score   </li> </ol>  <h4>Application Process</h4>  <table style=\"width: 100%;\">   <tbody>     <tr>       <td>Stage</td>       <td>Process</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>1</td>       <td>         Online Application- Select your university and course and fill the         university form       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>2</td>       <td>         Admission offer letter- Once the university completes the screening, the         candidate is given an admission letter to join the university       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>3</td>       <td>         Payment- Once the admission the confirm the candidate is required to pay         the fee       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>4</td>       <td>         Completion of documents- Apply for Visa, Bank loans, Medical test, and         Insurance, etc.       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>5</td>       <td>Join the University</td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table>  <h3>Northern State Medical University Fees Structure</h3>  <table style=\"width: 100%;\">   <tbody>     <tr>       <th>Particulars</th>       <th>Tuition Fee / Year</th>       <th>Hostel Fee /Year</th>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>Fees In US Dollars</strong></td>       <td>5500 USD</td>       <td>1000 USD</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td><strong>Fees In Rupees (INR) Approx.</strong></td>       <td>3,85,000 Rupees/yr.</td>       <td>70,000 Rupees/yr.</td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table>  <p>   <strong>MBBS Experts</strong>&nbsp;would like to bring to your notice that   the&nbsp;<strong>Tuition Fee</strong>&nbsp;for the&nbsp;<strong     >MBBS Course</strong   >&nbsp;or other Courses may vary depending on the&nbsp;<strong     >Exchange Rates</strong   >&nbsp;of Indian Rupee against USD. Exchange rates are volatile and are   subject to change from time to time. Kindly check the&nbsp;<strong     >Exchange Rates</strong   >&nbsp;before initiating the admission process. Also, note that the   University/College reserves all the rights to amend the tuition fees anytime   without any prior personal intimation to the students. </p>  <h4>Why Russia is the Top Choice for MBBS Studies Abroad?</h4>  <p>   There are many reasons for opting for a medical degree in Russia. Russia is a   superpower and its institutions have gained good name and fame at the   international level. Pursuing MBBS in Russia can open different options for   medical students. Some of the major reasons making Russia best for MBBS   Studies are: </p>  <ol>   <li>     The medical colleges in Russia offer world class education and they are     packed with advanced technology as well as equipment which are highly     beneficial for the students.   </li>   <li>Around 30 medical institutions in Russia have international ranking</li>   <li>     The medical universities in Russia have been recognised by international     agencies like WHO, medical councils of other countries and the National     Medical Commission (NMC)   </li>   <li>     The low cost fee structure of the top and best Russia MBBS colleges as     compared to the Indian private medical universities is the key reason as to     why the students opt to study medical in Russia.   </li>   <li>     There are a number of modern hospitals available in the nation for the     purpose of doing internship during MBBS in Russia   </li>   <li>     The campus as well as the overall environment is friendly to the students at     the time of medical study in Russia   </li>   <li>     MBBS study in Russia is completely safe as well as secure for the foreign     students which is a great sign of relief and certainly advantageous   </li>   <li>     Russia MBBS provides the opportunity to the students to have an interaction     with some of the renowned personalities in the field of medicine   </li>   <li>     MBBS in Russia would necessarily provide Indian students with a global     exposure which would be great for their future and career   </li>   <li>     The best Russia universities for medicine are top rankers of the world and     hence the students get a chance to study at some of the top universities of     the world.   </li>   <li>Medical universities in Russia offer education in English medium</li>   <li>     Russia provides a very suitable social environment for international     students   </li> </ol>  <h4>About The City</h4>  <p>   Arkhangelsk or Archangel in English is the administrative centre in the north   of European Russia. The city serves as the administrative block of Oblast. The   city is situated on the bank of Northern Dvina River and is spread in an area   of 40 kilometres. The city is a home of many reputable institutions and   Northern State medical university is one of them. The international airport is   located near to the city. The city has very good and planned infrastructure   and it is convenient to explore the city. Many cultural and festive activities   are organised </p>  <h4>Climate</h4>  <p>   The weather is mostly cold. The winter season is slightly extended. There is   White Sea which is 40 KM away from the city which leads to humid weather and   frequent rainfall. The city mostly remains cold so one needs good stock of   warm clothes to stay in the city. The weather is cold but it won&rsquo;t stop   you from exploring the city as it has a good network of public transport which   is functional throughout the year. </p>', 'NORTHERN STATE MEDICAL UNIVERSITY | IMC Consultancy', 'The Northern State Medical University is a high-quality institution of medical education in Russia. It is situated in the northern part of Russia and it also offers an amalgamation of Russian and European education.'),
(18, 'INGUSH STATE UNIVERSITY', 1, 'INGUSH-State-Medical-University-RUSSIA.png', 3, '<p>   This institution is a public health university. Ingushetia Medical State   University first opened its doors in 1994. It&rsquo;s located in the city of   Megas, Russian Federation. One of Russia&rsquo;s newest public universities   can be found right here. It has more academic offerings than any other local   university, with 10 schools and 42 departments available throughout its   several sites. </p> <p>   Ingush State Medical University is among the universities that have been   recognized by many bodies, including the World Health Organization (WHO), the   Ministry of Science and Higher Education of the Russian Federation (MoSHE),   the National Medical Commission (NMC), etc. Following graduation from Ingush   State University in Russia with an MBBS, students can choose to do their   clinical rotations in India. </p> <h3>   So why should medical school hopefuls from India think about Ingush State   Medical University Russia? </h3> <p>   The MBBS program at Ingush state medical university Russia is attracting a   growing number of international students because of the increased number of   attractive features offered by this university. Recently, this school has   become increasingly popular among students planning to enter the medical   field. </p> <h3>Here are some interesting details you should be aware of:</h3> <p>Instructional feature</p> <p>   In addition to students from India, the university&rsquo;s faculty of medicine   welcomes students from all around the world because it provides its entire   medical curriculum in English. </p> <h4>Period of Instruction</h4> <p>   An MBBS degree from Ingush State Medical University takes a full six years to   complete. </p> <h5>Those Learning in another Country</h5> <p>   More international students choose to attend this school to study a wide range   of disciplines. As of right now, we have more than 5,000 students enrolled. A   huge number of international students apply each year to study in a wide range   of academic program. </p> <h5>The MBBS Program Acceptance Requirements</h5> <p>When all five conditions are met, the acceptance procedure is complete.</p> <h6>TO REGISTER AT INGUSH STATE UNIVERSITY, PLEASE FOLLOW THESE STEPS:</h6> <p>When all five conditions are met, the acceptance procedure is complete.</p> <p>   As a first step in the admission process, students must complete an online   application. </p> <p>   Task number two: processing your invitation letter after carefully filling out   the application form and paying the fee of $500 usd, you will be able to   acquire the letter of invitation. Step </p> <p>   When a student receives an invitation letter from the Russian Education   Center, the following step is to apply for a visa. </p> <p>   The Fourth Step is Enrolment and the Start of Classes Each student needs to   provide their First Year Expenses receipt in addition to their complete set of   documents. A complete file of documents and an itemized budget for the first   academic year must be submitted after the student arrives in Russia. The   required steps for transferring credit are carried out exclusively at the   Russia education center. </p> <p>   Check the Ingush state medical university fee structure in detail before you   apply. </p> <h4>Ingush State Medical University Russia MBBS Fee Structure</h4>    <table width=\"100%\">     <thead>       <tr>         <th scope=\"col\">Ingush State Medical University</th>         <th scope=\"col\">1st Year Fees</th>         <th scope=\"col\">2st Year Fees</th>         <th scope=\"col\">3st Year Fees</th>         <th scope=\"col\">4st Year Fees</th>         <th scope=\"col\">5st Year Fees</th>         <th scope=\"col\">6st Year Fees</th>       </tr>       <tr>         <td>Tuition Fees</td>         <td>180,000 Ruble</td>         <td>180,000 Ruble</td>         <td>180,000 Ruble</td>         <td>180,000 Ruble</td>         <td>180,000 Ruble</td>         <td>180,000 Ruble</td>       </tr>       <tr>         <td>Hostel Fees</td>         <td>30,000 Ruble</td>         <td>30,000 Ruble</td>         <td>30,000 Ruble</td>         <td>30,000 Ruble</td>         <td>30,000 Ruble</td>         <td>30,000 Ruble</td>       </tr>       <tr>         <td>Total MBBS Fees</td>         <td>210,000 Ruble</td>         <td>210,000 Ruble</td>         <td>210,000 Ruble</td>         <td>210,000 Ruble</td>         <td>210,000 Ruble</td>         <td>210,000 Ruble</td>       </tr>     </thead>   </table>  <p>Medical insurance + Medical checkup &ndash; 200 $/year</p> <p>Ingush Medical State University fully English medium University</p> <p>   <strong>Tuition Fees</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; Includes Examination Fee, Study   Materials, Library Charge<br /><strong>Hostel Fee&nbsp;</strong>&ndash;   Includes Accommodation, Bedding, Furniture, 24 Hours Electricity, 24 Hours Gas   supply in Separate Kitchen, 24 Hours Hot and Cold water supply and Room   heating system.<br /><strong>Food Fees</strong>&nbsp;&ndash; 100 US   Dollars/month = RS 8000 Per Month </p> <p>   If you are also looking out to leverage the benefit of matured experience on   medicinal education in Russia, then come and speak to our admission   consultants. </p> <p>   <strong>Accommodation</strong><br />Ingush State Medical University provides a   hostel for all foreign and Russian students who are nearby to the university   and the hostels are very hygienic and, in terms of security, very reliable.   Special attention to all girls students&rsquo; safety. Ingush State Medical   University hostel rooms are neat and clean hostel rooms. At Ingush State   Medical University a Indian mess facility is available. Healthy and delicious   Indian food is available for all Indian students. Indian food in Russia is   cooked with special care of hygiene and quality. </p>', 'INGUSH STATE UNIVERSITY | IMC Consultancy', 'This institution is a public health university. Ingushetia Medical State University first opened its doors in 1994. It’s located in the city of Megas, Russian Federation. One of Russia’s newest public universities can be found right here. ');
