(19, 'KATHMANDU UNIVERSITY SCHOOL OF MEDICAL SCIENCES', 1, 'Kathmandu-University-School-of-Medical-Sciences.png', 4, '<p>   The cooperation initiative between Kathmandu University and Dhulikhel Hospital   led to the creation of the Kathmandu University School of Medical Sciences   (KUSMS). Dhulikhel Medical Center One of the first institutions in Nepal was   founded and is sponsored by the Dhulikhel neighborhood: Kathmandu University   Hospital. </p> <p>   This non-governmental organization strives to be non-profit. The hospital was   built in 1996 as a result of a partnership between the municipality of   Dhulikhel, Nepali Med International, and Dhulikhel Health Service Association,   under the direction of the late king, HM Birender Bir Bikram Shah Dev. The   hospital offers quality, affordable, compassionate healthcare services with   qualified employees. </p> <p>   The hospital is a testament to the idea that high-quality healthcare   doesn&rsquo;t necessarily have to be a costly luxury available exclusively to   the wealthy. For MBBS studies in Nepal, Kathmandu University School of Medical   Sciences is a fantastic option. The university is a great place to pursue a   career in medicine because it has top-notch educational facilities and   cutting-edge teaching approaches. Students praise the faculty for being   friendly, assured, knowledgeable in their fields, and down to earth. Every   year, applicants from India and other countries apply for admission to the   MBBS Program. </p> <p>   The Kathmandu University Nepal is made up of numerous faculties and   departments that educate qualified specialists in the majority of the   country&rsquo;s economic sectors. More than 100 doctors who teach medical   disciplines in Bengali and English are part of the workforce. It is a higher   education facility committed to upholding the bar for academic achievement   across a range of traditional and contemporary fields. </p> <h2><strong>About Kathmandu University School of Medical Science</strong></h2>  <table style=\"width: 100%;\">   <thead></thead>   <tbody>     <tr>       <td>Name of Institute</td>       <td>Kathmandu University School of Medical Sciences</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Popular Name</td>       <td>KUSMS, Kathmandu University</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Location</td>       <td>Dhulikhel, Bagmati, Nepal</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Year of Establishment</td>       <td>1991</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Kathmandu University Ranking</td>       <td>Country- 01, World- 4532</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Institute Type</td>       <td>Public</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Courses offered</td>       <td>MBBS</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Hostel Facilities</td>       <td>Yes</td>     </tr>   </tbody>   <tfoot></tfoot> </table>  <h2>   <strong>Kathmandu University School of Medical Sciences Ranking</strong> </h2> <p>   Kathmandu University School of Medical Sciences in Nepal enjoys a good ranking   and has built a strong reputation in the field of education. The institution   is well-regarded for the quality of education it provides, making it a   favourable choice for students seeking academic excellence in Nepal. With a   good ranking and a positive reputation, Kathmandu University School of Medical   Sciences stands as a reliable option for those looking to pursue higher   education in the country. </p> <h2><strong>Study MBBS in Nepal</strong></h2> <p>   The MBBS program in Nepal typically follows a structured curriculum, and   I&rsquo;ve simplified the information you provided for easier understanding: </p> <h3>   <strong>Academics of Kathmandu University School of Medical Sciences</strong> </h3> <ul>   <li>     Duration: Four and a half years, followed by a 1-year compulsory residential     rotating internship.   </li>   <li>Language of Instruction: English</li> </ul> <h3><strong>Preclinical Curriculum (Semesters 1-4)</strong></h3> <ul>   <li>     First and second years include subjects like Anatomy, Microbiology,     Pathology, Pharmacology, and Physiology.   </li>   <li>     These subjects are integrated and taught alongside Community Medicine and     Introduction to Clinical Medicine.   </li>   <li>     Medical Informatics is integrated to provide computer expertise relevant to     medical education.   </li>   <li>     University examinations are held at the end of the first and second years.   </li>   <li>     Students must complete all preclinical subjects within specified timeframes.   </li> </ul> <h3><strong>Clinical Sciences (Semesters 5-9)</strong></h3> <ul>   <li>     Clinical subjects include Forensic Medicine, Community Medicine,     Ophthalmology, Medicine &amp; Allied Subjects, Psychiatry, Dermatology,     Radiology, Emergency Medicine, Obstetrics &amp; Gynecology, Pediatrics, and     other specialties.   </li>   <li>     Third-year university examinations are held for Forensic Medicine, Community     Medicine, and Ophthalmology.   </li>   <li>     A student cannot progress to the ninth semester without passing these     subjects.   </li>   <li>     Ninth semester includes final university examinations in Medicine, Surgery,     Obstetrics, Gynecology, and Pediatrics.   </li> </ul> <h3><strong>Evaluation</strong></h3> <ul>   <li>     Continuous evaluation is conducted through fortnightly tests, semester     exams, end-posting evaluations, seminars, and problem-based learning     sessions.   </li>   <li>     The continuous evaluation system contributes to excellent results in     university examinations.   </li> </ul> <h3><strong>Teaching Methodology</strong></h3> <ul>   <li>     Preclinical teaching includes didactic classroom lectures, practical     sessions, problem-based learning (PBL) sessions, and community/hospital     visits.   </li>   <li>     Seminars and PBLs are conducted every fortnight to provide clinical     orientation.   </li>   <li>     Clinical teaching involves practical training in hospitals, community     visits, symposia, seminars, clinical meetings, faculty talks, and guest     lectures.   </li>   <li>An emphasis is placed on clinical practical training.</li> </ul> <h3><strong>Internship</strong></h3> <ul>   <li>A one-year rotating internship is compulsory.</li>   <li>     Different internship schemes are approved for students from various     countries.   </li>   <li>     Internships can be completed in Nepal, India, Sri Lanka, Australia, USA, UK,     and South Africa.   </li>   <li>     Internship rules are subject to change based on the regulations of the     Medical Council of Nepal.   </li> </ul> <h2>   <strong>Kathmandu University School of Medical Science Fee Structure</strong> </h2> <p>   The fees for the undergraduate medical program at Kathmandu University School   of Medical Sciences are listed below: </p>  <table style=\"width: 100%;\">   <thead>     <tr>       <th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\">Course</th>       <th colspan=\"1\" rowspan=\"1\">Total tuition fee</th>     </tr>   </thead>   <tbody>     <tr>       <td>MBBS</td>       <td>Rs 41,68,090/-</td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table>  <h2>   <strong     >Admission Procedure For Kathmandu University School of Medical     Sciences</strong   > </h2> <ul>   <li>     Application forms for admission into medical colleges in Nepal are typically     available in September/October.   </li>   <li>     Applicants can collect these forms from authorized centers in India and     abroad.   </li>   <li>     The filled application form should be accompanied by various documents,     including a passport or Aadhar card, a recent passport-size photo, and     attested copies of 10th and 12th-grade mark sheets.   </li>   <li>     An application fee of INR 5000 payable to the Medical Education Commission,     Nepal, is required.   </li>   <li>     If applying for direct admission based on NEET scores, candidates need to     include their NEET scorecard.   </li> </ul> <p>   <strong>Notes:<br /></strong> </p> <ul>   <li>     The MEC entrance exam is conducted only in Nepal, so applicants from other     countries need to travel there to take the exam.   </li>   <li>     If there are more applicants through the MEC entrance examination compared     to direct NEET admission, priority will be given to candidates who have     qualified through the entrance exam.   </li> </ul> <h2>   <strong     >Eligibility Criteria For Kathmandu University School of Medical     Science</strong   > </h2> <p>   Admission to medical colleges MBBS in Nepal for Indian students follows two   main pathways: one through an entrance examination conducted by the Medical   Education Commission (MEC) and the other through direct admission based on   NEET scores for Indian students. Here&rsquo;s a simplified explanation: </p> <h3>   <strong>Direct Admission Through NEET Scores for Indian Students:</strong> </h3> <ul>   <li>     Indian students seeking direct admission to private medical colleges in     Nepal can do so based on their NEET scores.   </li>   <li>     The MBBS course duration is 4.5 years, followed by a 1-year internship.   </li>   <li>     Eligibility criteria include passing 10+2 with Physics, Chemistry, and     Biology with a 50% aggregate or equivalent grades from certificate-level     programs.   </li>   <li>     Candidates should be at least 17 years old by the application deadline.   </li> </ul> <h3><strong>Admission Through MEC Entrance Examination:</strong></h3> <ul>   <li>     Students interested in studying MBBS in specific Nepalese institutions like     BP Koirala Institute of Health Science, Dharan Institute of Medical Science,     Patan Academy of Health Science, Kamali Academy of Health Science, Nepalese     Army Institute of Health Science, and Kathmandu University School of Medical     Science need to take the MEC entrance examination.   </li>   <li>     To qualify, candidates must score a minimum of 50% in this entrance exam.   </li>   <li>     Only NEET scores from the current academic year will be considered for     admission.   </li>   <li>     The minimum NEET score required for general category candidates will     determine their eligibility.   </li> </ul> <h2>   <strong>Documents Required For&nbsp;</strong   ><strong>Kathmandu University School of Medical Science&nbsp;</strong   ><strong>Admission</strong> </h2> <ul>   <li>Passport</li>   <li>10th mark sheet and certificate.</li>   <li>12th mark sheet and certificate.</li>   <li>Birth certificate</li>   <li>10th passport-size photographs</li>   <li>     Official invitation letter from the Kathmandu University School of Medical     Science.   </li>   <li>Verified documents from the Ministry of External Affairs, New Delhi</li>   <li>Verified documents by the Nepal Embassy.</li>   <li>Visa fees</li>   <li>Bank receipt of the paid tuition fee of 1st year.</li> </ul> <h2>   <strong     >Advantages of Studying at Kathmandu University School of Medical     Science</strong   > </h2> <ul>   <li>     The MBBS program at Kathmandu University School of Medical Sciences has     various benefits.   </li>   <li>     Students from Indian regions find it easier to study because MBBS at     universities follows the same Indian Pattern in every manner.   </li>   <li>     Since India is a neighboring country, there are many Indian lecturers and     staff members in the university as well as many Indian students that are     enrolled there.   </li>   <li>     In comparison to other universities in Nepal, there are too many students     passing.   </li>   <li>     The fact that the tuition for medical programs at Dhulikhel Hospital     Kathmandu University is reasonable and that scholarships are available to     students is another advantage.   </li> </ul> <h2><strong>Faculty &amp; Staff</strong></h2> <p>   Kathmandu University School of Medical Sciences in Nepal offers a wide array   of facilities to cater to the diverse needs of its students. These encompass a   dedicated medical centre to address health concerns, a comprehensive library   to support academic research, a spacious auditorium for various events and   gatherings, comfortable hostel options for accommodation, advanced computer   labs for technology-driven learning, sports facilities to promote physical   well-being, a convenient cafeteria for dining, and well-equipped laboratories   for practical experiments and research. These facilities collectively   contribute to creating a conducive and enriching environment for both academic   and personal growth. </p> <h2><strong>Student Support</strong></h2> <p>   Kathmandu University School of Medical Sciences offers a range of support   services for its students. These services include anti-ragging measures to   ensure a safe environment, counselling services for guidance and support,   access to healthcare facilities, assistance with hostel accommodations, a   platform for reporting issues and asking questions, and even local language   learning classes. Whether you need help with personal or academic matters, we   are here to provide the support you need during your time at the college. </p>', 'KATHMANDU UNIVERSITY SCHOOL OF MEDICAL SCIENCES | IMC Consultancy', 'Kathmandu University School of Medical Sciences in Nepal enjoys the best ranking and has built a strong reputation in the field of education. The institution is well-regarded for the quality of education it provides'),
(20, 'KATHMANDU MEDICAL COLLEGE', 1, 'Kathmandu-University-Nepal.png', 4, '<p>The Kathmandu medical college also known as KMCTH is a medical institute that is located in the country capital of Kathmandu. The Kathmandu medical college is a private medical college in Nepal. This medical university was established in the year 1997 and is being providing excellent medical education since.</p> <p>The Kathmandu medical college, Kathmandu is affiliated with Kathmandu University and is also recognized by international organizations such as the medical council of Nepal, Sri Lankan medical council, general medical council, and also the medical council of India. The university is also been listed in the WHO&rsquo;s world directory of medical schools, the international medical education directory, and many more.</p> <p>The Kathmandu national medical college has a teaching hostel that is used to provide extensive training and to the students who study&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mbbsadmissionabroad.in/mbbs-in-nepal\"><strong>MBBS in Nepal</strong></a>. Students learn by training under professionals who excel in the medical field.</p> <h3><strong>Kathmandu Medical College Quick Glance:</strong></h3> <p>The following mentioned below are the highlights at a Quick Glance about the Kathmandu medical college:</p>   <table style=\"width: 100%;\"> <tbody> <tr> <td colspan=\"3\"> <h4>Kathmandu Medical College Quick Glance</h4> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>University Name:</strong></td> <td>Kathmandu Medical College, Nepal</td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Type:</strong></td> <td>Private</td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Eligibility criteria:</strong></td> <td> <ul> <li>&nbsp;An aggregate of 50% in 10+2 or HSE</li> <li>&nbsp;Must have PCB as the main subject in 10+2</li> </ul> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>NEET examination required:</strong></td> <td>Yes, the required score in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mbbsadmissionabroad.in/nta-neet-exam-pattern-syllabus-preparation-tips\"><strong>NEET exam</strong></a>&nbsp;is required</td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Entrance examination required:</strong></td> <td>Not required</td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Approved by:</strong></td> <td> <ul> <li>&nbsp;Medical council of Nepal</li> <li>&nbsp;World health organization&nbsp;</li> <li>&nbsp;Medical council of India</li> <li>&nbsp;General medical council</li> </ul> </td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>The medium of education:</strong></td> <td>English and Nepali language</td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Course duration:</strong></td> <td>5 years</td> </tr> <tr> <td><strong>Country ranking</strong></td> <td>1st position in country rankings</td> </tr> </tbody> </table>   <h3><strong>Why Choose Kathmandu Medical College Nepal?</strong></h3> <p>It is one of the top listed medical institutes for foreign students who wish to pursue MBBS in Nepal. The college is recognized with NMC formally known as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.mbbsadmissionabroad.in/mci-nmc-approved-medical-colleges-mbbs-in-abroad-list\"><strong>MCI</strong></a>&nbsp;and offers the best medical education in the country. The degree holder from the college can apply for a job anywhere in the world.</p> <ul> <li>&nbsp;The College library has a vast collection of books for students.</li> <li>&nbsp;Programs are taught in the English language.</li> <li>&nbsp;No requirement to qualify for any English language test.</li> <li>&nbsp;The cost of the study is low as compared to medical colleges in Nepal.</li> <li>&nbsp;Listed in top medical colleges in Nepal.</li> <li>&nbsp;Good environment for Indian students.</li> <li>&nbsp;Recognized by NMC or MCI.</li> <li>&nbsp;Provide globally approved medical degrees.</li> <li>&nbsp;Qualified and well-experienced teachers for quality education.</li> <li>&nbsp;The best accommodation is available for foreign students.</li> </ul> <h3><strong>Kathmandu Medical College Ranking:</strong></h3> <p>According to the Kathmandu medical college ranking, the university is in the 1<sup>st</sup>&nbsp;position in the country of Nepal and is also on the world university ranking at the 6543 positions.</p> <h3><strong>Kathmandu Medical College Fee Structure 2022:</strong></h3> <p>The following mentioned below is the Kathmandu medical college fee structure for MBBS along with detailed and information such as its tuition fees, hostel, and food cost:</p> <h3><strong>Kathmandu Medical College Courses</strong></h3> <p>Kathmandu Medical College is affiliated with Kathmandu University offers undergraduate, postgraduate, and other special programs to students. The college offers MBBS and BDS Programs to candidates who wish to study in Nepal. Both the programs take four and a half years duration of time to complete. As the college is recognized by WHO &amp; NMC so the courses offered here are globally accepted.&nbsp;</p> <p>Candidates can check below the Kathmandu Medical College Courses that are available for the aspirants:</p>   <table style=\"width: 100%;\"> <tbody> <tr> <td colspan=\"2\"> <h4>Kathmandu Medical College Courses</h4> </td> </tr> <tr> <td> <h4>Courses</h4> </td> <td> <h4>Duration</h4> </td> </tr> <tr> <td> <p>MBBS Program</p> </td> <td> <p>5 Years</p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td> <p>BDS Program</p> </td> <td> <p>4 Years 6 Months</p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td> <p>PG Program</p> </td> <td> <p>3 Years</p> </td> </tr> <tr> <td> <p>Nursing Program</p> </td> <td> <p>4 Years</p> </td> </tr> </tbody> </table>   <h3><strong>Kathmandu Medical College Eligibility Criteria:</strong></h3> <p>The following mentioned below is the eligibility criteria for Kathmandu medical college admission to study MBBS in Nepal:</p> <ul> <li>&nbsp;The age of the applicant should be above 17 years in age</li> <li>&nbsp;The applicant must have completed their 10+2 or higher secondary education from a recognized board</li> <li>&nbsp;The applicant must have chemistry, physics, and biology as their main subjects in 10 + 2</li> <li>&nbsp;The applicant must get a min. the score of 50% in the higher secondary examination or 10 + 2</li> <li>&nbsp;The applicant must get a valid score in the NEET entrance examination to get admission and study MBBS in Nepal</li> </ul> <h3><strong>Admission Process for Kathmandu Medical College 2022:</strong></h3> <p>Plans to study MBBS in abroad? Then you can check the Kathmandu Medical College information. Also, You can connect with our expert counselors to get more info on MBBS Admission in Nepal by&nbsp;<a data-toggle=\"modal\" data-target=\"#myModal2\">clicking here</a>.</p> <h3><strong>Kathmandu Medical College Documents Required:</strong></h3> <p>The following mentioned below is the list of all the documents that are required by the Kathmandu school of medical sciences for MBBS admission in Nepal:</p> <ul> <li>&nbsp;Passport of the applicant which has a minimum validity of 18 months.</li> <li>&nbsp;Certificate of 10<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;and 12<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;mark sheet of the applicant.</li> <li>&nbsp;Birth certificate of the candidate</li> <li>&nbsp;Pas port sized photographs of the applicant</li> <li>&nbsp;Invitation letter from the medical college in Nepal.</li> <li>&nbsp;The application documents should be authorized by the ministry of external affairs</li> <li>&nbsp;All documents are too legalized by the Nepali embassy.</li> <li>&nbsp;Medical certificate of the candidate along with the HIV test documents</li> </ul> <h3><strong>Benefits of Studying in this University:</strong></h3> <p>The following mentioned below is the Benefits of Study MBBS at Kathmandu school of medical sciences:</p> <ul> <li>&nbsp;No donations are accepted by the MBBS college in Kathmandu Nepal</li> <li>&nbsp;The college is affiliated with the Tribhuvan University and offers education to study MBBS in Nepal.</li> <li>&nbsp;The Kathmandu medical college is recognized by international organizations such as the world health organization, the medical council of India, medical council of Nepal.</li> <li>&nbsp;The university uses English as their medium of education, which attracts students from all over the world.</li> <li>&nbsp;The Kathmandu medical college is affiliated with several hospitals that are used to give in-field training to all the medical students</li> <li>&nbsp;The Kathmandu medical college is known to offer excellent quality of education</li> <li>&nbsp;The university offers hostel facilities that have fully furnished and modern rooms</li> </ul> <h3><strong>Kathmandu Medical College Students Life:</strong></h3> <p>The following is a list of all the activities and the surrounding environment offered to provide a better experience for all its students who study MBBS in Nepal in Kathmandu medical college:</p> <ul> <li>&nbsp;The college campus offers canteen and mess facilities.</li> <li>&nbsp;The university offers all its students with hostel facility that is fully equitized and have all the modern accommodates</li> <li>&nbsp;The campus of the university has a playground and a gym for all its students</li> <li>&nbsp;The MBBS college in Nepal are affiliated hospitals that are used to provide training to the students</li> <li>&nbsp;The campus is surrounded by restaurants that provide great food</li> </ul> <h3><strong>Kathmandu Medical College Hostel and Accommodation:</strong></h3> <p>The following is the Hostel and Accommodation offered by the Kathmandu medical college is as follows:</p> <ul> <li>&nbsp;Have separate hostels for male and females.</li> <li>&nbsp;The hostels are provided with fully furnished hostel rooms</li> <li>&nbsp;There is options for Air-conditioned rooms</li> <li>&nbsp;The hostel of Nepal medical college have mess facilities for its students</li> <li>&nbsp;The hostels are fully protected and have a good security system</li> <li>&nbsp;The hostels are provided with water and electricity</li> </ul>', 'KATHMANDU MEDICAL COLLEGE | IMC Consultancy', 'The Kathmandu Medical College also known as KMCTH is a medical institute that is located in the country capital of Kathmandu. Provides best education in medical sciences.'),
(21, 'CHITWAN MEDICAL COLLEGE', 1, 'Chitwan-medical-college-nepal.png', 4, '<p>   Chitwan Medical College is a private medical institute in Bharatpur, Nepal. It   is affiliated to Tribhuvan University. This is the first medical institution   to have an ISO certification in Nepal. This college is a result of the joint   efforts of a team of medical professionals who envisioned an institution in   the valley to impart quality education and provide affordable health care   services to the population of Chitwan. The foundation of this institution was   laid in 2006. BNS program was commenced in the same year. In 2019, the   institution was upgraded to a 750 beds hospital. The hospital registers a   footfall of 1500 patients every day. This college has the necessary   infrastructure like lecture halls, seminar rooms, libraries and laboratories   etc. Chitwan Medical College (CMC) is known for its commitment to prepare   competent medical professionals and provide quality health care services to   people. Studying medicine in Chitwan Medical College will make you feel that   the teachers care a lot for the international students and they are always   ready to help at any point of time. This benefits the international students   in a number of ways and is good for their successful medical career. Many   Students from the different states in India enrol every year for the MBBS   studies in Nepal. </p> <h3>Programs</h3> <p>   <u     >Various academic courses are offered at Chitwan Medical College. The list     of the courses includes:</u   > </p> <ol>   <li>Bachelor of Nursing (BNS)</li>   <li>B.Sc. in Nursing</li>   <li>Bachelor of Medicine and Bachelor of Surgery (MBBS)</li>   <li>Bachelors in Medical Laboratory Technology (B.Sc. MLT)</li>   <li>Bachelor in Dental Surgery (BDS)</li>   <li>Bachelor in Pharmacy</li>   <li>Masters in Public Health</li> </ol> <h3>Accreditations and Recognition</h3> <p>   <u     >Chitwan Medical College has been recognized by the following agencies and     departments:</u   > </p> <ol>   <li>It is Nepal&rsquo;s first ISO certified medical institution</li>   <li>It is affiliated to Tribhuvan University, Nepal</li>   <li>Nepal Medical Council</li>   <li>Nepal Nursing Council</li>   <li>Nepal Pharmacy Council</li>   <li>Lincoln University, UK</li>   <li>It has been recognized by the National Medical Commission (NMC)</li> </ol> <h3>Facilities in the CMC</h3> <ol>   <li>     <strong>Library Facility-</strong>&nbsp;The library at CMC is well organized     and has a plentiful supply of books for the students. The catalogs are based     on the Dewey Decimal Classification System. The library facility is     available at two locations; one is at the college and the other library is     in the hospital. The library timings are from 7 AM to 12 PM.   </li>   <li>     <strong>Hostel-</strong>&nbsp;The hostel facility is available for both boys     and girls. It has a capacity to accommodate around 1000 students. The rooms     are given for twin occupancy.   </li>   <li>     <strong>Canteen-</strong>&nbsp;The canteen facility is very good. There is a     canteen for each hostel building and a separate canteen at the college and     hospital also. The food served is hygienic and offers variety. A monthly     charge of Nepali Rs. 6000 needs to be paid by the student.   </li>   <li>     <strong>IT services and Transport facility-</strong>&nbsp;IT services are     available for all the students at CMC. More than a hundred computer systems     and a WIFI zone have been set us at the campus. The students are provided     their login ID and password so that they can access the online services. Bus     service is provided to take students from the college campus to the     hospital.   </li> </ol> <h3>Location</h3> <p>   Chitwan Medical College is located in Bharatpur, Nepal. Bharatpur is the   fourth largest city of Nepal. The city lies on the bank of Narayani River and   it is one of the fastest-growing cities of Nepal. There are many places of   tourist attractions. The city has good infrastructure and a good public   transport system as well. </p> <h3>Why Indian Students Prefer MBBS Study from Nepal?</h3> <ol>   <li>     The country offers rewarding career opportunities to medical graduates   </li>   <li>Medical graduates can also go for PG and MD courses</li>   <li>Highly sophisticated education facilities</li>   <li>Safe nation for male and female medical aspirants</li>   <li>The fees structure of the medical universities is low</li>   <li>Good and reasonably priced accommodation facility available</li>   <li>All modern infrastructure readily available</li>   <li>Safe and peaceful atmosphere good for studies</li>   <li>Cooperative and qualified faculties to assist</li>   <li>Instruction in English for the international medical candidates</li>   <li>Accommodation cost is also not very high</li>   <li>Superb education facilities with necessary practical training</li> </ol> <h3>More About the MBBS Program in CMC</h3> <p>   The MBBS program at Chitwan Medical College started in 2006 with an intake of   80 students. The MBBS course is designed to train medical professionals who   are knowledgeable and use critical thinking in the clinical decision-making   process. The MBBS program CMC is based on the principles of student-centered   learning and community service. </p> <p><u>The goals of the MBBS course are to:</u></p> <ol>   <li>     To engage the learners and provide research-oriented medical education which     leads to the MBBS degree   </li>   <li>To train the students to deal with 21<sup>st</sup>-century challenges</li>   <li>     To ingrain the values like Compassion, Service, and ethical outlook in the     medical professionals   </li> </ol> <h3>Duration of MBBS Study in CMC Nepal</h3> <p>   The duration of the MBBS program is 5.5 years. The 4.5 years are for the   theory and classroom training and it is followed by one-year compulsory   training. The internship starts right after the final exams and the candidate   receives a provisional registration number from Nepal Medical Council. The   internship period is divided according to the work experience needed for good   medical training. </p> <h3>MBBS Intake in CMC</h3> <p>   The annual intake of students for MBBS degree varies every year. On average   around 100-125 seats are available for this program. </p> <h3>Medium of Instruction</h3> <p>   The medium of instruction for the MBBS program is English. There is no need to   learn any local language or to pass any international language tests. You can   communicate in Hindi/English in the campus but the classroom instruction is   strictly English. </p> <h3>Eligibility</h3> <ol>   <li>     The eligibility for admission in the MBBS program is simple and basic.   </li>   <li>     A candidate should have scored 50 percent marks in class XII in the Science     stream.   </li>   <li>     The candidate should have studied Physics, Chemistry, Biology and English as     main subjects at class XII level.   </li>   <li>     The candidate also needs to clear the entrance test conducted by the     Institute of Medicine.   </li>   <li>     For Indian students, the NEET score for the same academic session will be     valid.&nbsp;   </li> </ol> <h3>Documents Required</h3> <p>   <u     >The admission process at CMC is simple. You need to submit the following     documents with the application form:</u   > </p> <ol>   <li>Class X mark sheet issued by the board</li>   <li>Class XII mark sheet issued by the board</li>   <li>Provisional certificate</li>   <li>A valid NEET scorecard for the current academic session</li>   <li>A copy of the Passport page</li>   <li>A medical certificate issued by a certified doctor</li> </ol> <h3>Admission Process</h3> <p>   <u     >The admission process begins in August and the deadline is usually around     10 September. The admission process is hassle-free. These are the following     steps need to be followed for securing a seat at CMC:</u   > </p> <ol>   <li>     The applications are invited in mid of August. The candidate should visit     the college website and fill the application form.   </li>   <li>     The mark sheets for class X and XII and the other relevant documents should     be scanned and uploaded with the application form.   </li>   <li>     A confirmation email will be sent by the college and the candidate should     visit the CMC campus with their parents to testify and present the original     documents.   </li>   <li>     The candidate will fill the other necessary documents and sign the agreement     of the rules and regulations.   </li>   <li>     The candidate will have to undergo a medical examination conducted at the     CMC campus. The successful candidates will be offered the final admission to     the MBBS course.   </li> </ol> <h3>More About Hostel in CMC</h3> <p>   <u     >The hostel facility at CMC is very good. The rooms are well-furnished and     ventilated. There 4 hostel buildings. Each building has three wings. Two     buildings are for boys&rsquo; hostel and two buildings are for girls&rsquo;     hostel. The following facilities are available in the hostel:</u   > </p> <ol>   <li>Recreation rooms</li>   <li>Dining hall with a common TV</li>   <li>Adequate storage and supply of clean drinking water</li>   <li>     Sports facility- Cricket, Soccer, Basket Ball, Volleyball, and table tennis,     etc.   </li> </ol> <h3>Why Indian Students Should Study at Chitwan Medical College?</h3> <ol>   <li>The medium of instruction is English.</li>   <li>There are no visa-related worries.</li>   <li>The admission process is simple and the NEET score is accepted.</li>   <li>Free from worry admission process for the MBBS course.</li>   <li>     The university do not demand for capitation or donation money apart from the     tuition fee.   </li>   <li>The university campus is safe for both boys and girls.</li>   <li>     The low fees structure in the medical universities is a major attraction.   </li>   <li>     Not only the tuition fee for the MBBS course but also the accommodation     expenses are low   </li>   <li>     High standard of the education in the field of medicine. The language of     instruction for the foreign students is English which abolished the problem     of language barrier.   </li>   <li>     Safe, engaging, and health study atmosphere suitable for male and female     medical students.   </li>   <li>     The university is approved by the National Medical Commission beneficial     particularly for the Indian medical students.   </li>   <li>It has been recognized by the National Medical Commission (NMC).</li>   <li>The hostel facility is easily available.</li>   <li>     The world class education along with premium facilities for the students     make CMC one of the most obvious medicine study destinations in Nepal.   </li> </ol>', 'CHITWAN MEDICAL COLLEGE | IMC Consultancy', 'Chitwan Medical College (CMC) is known for its commitment to preparing competent medical professionals and providing quality medical education.');
