(113, 'ANDIJAN STATE MEDICAL INSTITUTE', 1, '', 7, '<h2><strong>About Andijan State Medical Institute</strong></h2> <p>   MBBS is a medical degree that must be acquired from a prestigious institute   for international recognition. Over lakhs of universities and institutes offer   medical courses around the globe but the need to check for the best suitable   for yourself is important. It is only possible if you have knowledge about the   universities and it is impossible for an&nbsp;MBBS&nbsp;aspirant to visit each   university in the world so essential information required about universities   or institutes is provided here. Today we have brought an institute from   Uzbekistan to your knowledge namely Andijan State Medical Institute. Andijan   State Medical Institute is one of the leading institute situated in the   ancient cities of Fergana Valley, Andijan City was founded in 1955. Andijan   State Medical Institute is a national institute in the Republic of Uzbekistan.   Andijan State Medical Institute is providing education in over 56 multiple   departments. </p> <h3>   <strong>More Information on Andijan Medical Institute : MBBS Course</strong> </h3>  <table>   <tbody>     <tr>       <td>Year of Establishment</td>       <td>1955</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Type</td>       <td>Government</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Recognition</td>       <td>NMC and WHO approved</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Eligibility</td>       <td>50% in Physics, Chemistry and Biology Aggregate</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Course Duration</td>       <td>6 Years</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>NEET</td>       <td>yes, compulsory</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>IELTS/TOFEL</td>       <td>Not Required</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Medium of Teaching</td>       <td>English</td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table>  <h3>   <strong     >Recognition and Accreditation of Andijan State Medical Institute</strong   > </h3> <p>   Andijan State Medical Institute recognized and accredited by various national   and international organizations such as the Medical Council of India (NMC),   World Health Organisations (WHO), and Ministry of Higher and Secondary   Specialized Education, Uzbekistan. </p> <h3><strong>Faculties of Andijan State Medical Institute:</strong></h3> <ul>   <li>Faculty of Medicine</li>   <li>Faculty of Paediatrics</li>   <li>Faculty of Dentistry</li>   <li>Faculty of Advanced training and retraining of physicians</li> </ul> <h3><strong>Andijan State Medical Institute MBBS Course Duration</strong></h3> <p>   Andijan State Medical Institute course duration is of complete 6 years which   is divided into 5 years of course and 1 year of internship. </p> <h3><strong>Reasons for Choosing Andijan State Medical Institute:</strong></h3> <ul>   <li>     Andijan State Medical Institute has a beautiful campus area within which     there are academic buildings and hostels.   </li>   <li>     Andijan State Medical Institute academic buildings have study classrooms,     well-equipped laboratories, and a library.   </li>   <li>     Andijan State Medical Institute imparts proper practical knowledge with     theoretical knowledge within students.   </li>   <li>     Students at Andijan State Medical Institute have multiple options to choose     from a wide range of specialization courses offered.   </li>   <li>     Andijan State Medical Institute has an enormous library providing 250000+     textbooks, references, journals, research papers, encyclopedias, editorials,     etc. Also, Andijan Medical Institute has reading halls and an electronic     library with the latest articles on medicine.   </li>   <li>     Andijan State Medical Institute has a huge team of highly qualified and     skilled professors.   </li>   <li>     Andijan State Medical Institute has tie-ups with other universities     providing a wide range of possibilities of great exposure and learning     through student exchange programs, scientific research.   </li>   <li>     In Andijan State Medical Institute, the medium of language used for     instructions in English.   </li> </ul> <h3><strong>Other facilities at Andijan State Medical Institute:</strong></h3> <ul>   <li>     Andijan State Medical Institute has hostel facilities for international     students.   </li>   <li>     Andijan State Medical Institute hostels have dormitories and fully furnished     rooms.   </li>   <li>     All the necessary facilities are provided at hostels such as Wi-Fi     connectivity, AC, heater, bed, cupboard, electric appliances, etc.   </li>   <li>     Andijan State Medical Institute cafeteria or canteen provides multiple     cuisines that too with proper care of hygiene.   </li>   <li>     Andijan State Medical Institute has a multicultural environment as students     from different parts of the world arrive at the Andijan State Medical     Institute for study.   </li> </ul> <h3>   <strong     >Eligibility Criteria for Andijan State Medical Institute Admission     2024-25:</strong   > </h3> <ul>   <li>     The minimum age for Andijan State Medical Institute admission is 17 years     and the maximum is 25 years.   </li>   <li>     The applicant must qualify for the&nbsp;NEET&nbsp;entrance examination with     a good score for the Andijan State Medical Institute admission.   </li>   <li>     The applicant must pass higher secondary school with a good percentage (at     least 50%).   </li> </ul> <h3>   <strong     >Documents Required for Andijan State Medical Institute Admission:</strong   > </h3> <ul>   <li>     Filled and signed application form taken from Andijan State Medical     Institute official website   </li>   <li>Copy of Higher Secondary School certificate</li>   <li>Copy of passport valid for a minimum of two years</li>   <li>Recent passport size photographs</li>   <li>Birth certificate</li>   <li>Medical certificate</li>   <li>Migration certificate</li> </ul> <h3><strong>Andijan State Medical Institute Admission Procedure:</strong></h3> <ul>   <li>     For the Andijan State Medical Institute admission procedure, first, an     applicant has to choose the course and then fill the application form and     mail it to the Andijan State Medical Institute attached with required     documents.   </li>   <li>     Once Andijan State Medical Institute receives mail and verifies the     documents, a confirmation mail is sent by Andijan State Medical Institute to     confirm the Andijan State Medical Institute admission.   </li>   <li>     After receiving the confirmation letter, the applicant must pay the Andijan     State Medical Institute fee according to the Andijan State Medical Institute     fee structure.   </li>   <li>     Then an invitation letter, visa support letter, and admission letter are     sent by courier to the applicant.   </li>   <li>     Once the invitation letter is received, the applicant must visit the embassy     for a visa application.   </li>   <li>     Andijan State Medical Institute admission procedure ends here by getting a     visa and then the applicant becomes a student of Andijan State Medical     Institute.   </li> </ul>', '', ''),
(114, 'FERGANA MEDICAL INSTITUTE OF PUBLIC HEALTH', 1, '', 7, '<p>   Studying MBBS Abroad and becoming a successful doctor is a dream for many   Indian students but choosing the right country makes their choice a little bit   difficult. But Fergana medical institute of Public health is helping you to   achieve your dream in the smartest way. </p>  <h2>MBBS Study In FERGANA MEDICAL INSTITUTE OF PUBLIC HEALTH</h2> <p>   Indian MBBS aspirants after completing their school studies appear in the NEET   UG Exam which is a single exam and basically a first step of entering the   Medical sphere&nbsp;Getting aware of the competition and huge budget of   studying MBBS from Indian private and government colleges, students have   started seeking other opportunities for studying Medicine and studying MBBS   Abroad has proven one of the best alternatives of MBBS in India.&nbsp;Now, the   question arises, which country would be the best fit for an Indian student.   Looking at all the benefits provided by other countries, Uzbekistan has   emerged as the most preferred destination for students and specially Fergana   medical college holds the top position among the other medical colleges of   Uzbekistan, because it perfectly fits the guidelines of the national medical   council of India issued in the New NMC Gazette 2021. </p>  <h3>Eligibility criteria for Fergana medical institute of Public health</h3>  To get admission to MBBS in Uzbekistan (Fergana medical institute of Public health) students need to fulfil the following criteria: <ul>   <li>Candidate must not be below 17 years of age</li>   <li>Candidate must have scored 50% in 12th</li>   <li>     Reserved category candidates like OBC, SC, ST, he must have scored 40% marks     in 12th with PCB.   </li>   <li>The primary subjects in 12th should be Physics, Chemistry, Biology</li>   <li>The candidates should have cleared the NEET UG exam</li>   <li>NEET scorecard should not be older than 3 years.</li> </ul>  <h3>Admission process to Fergana Medical Institute of Public Health</h3>  <ul>   <li>     First of all, the candidates need to select the university and submit the     application online.   </li>   <li>     After successful completion of the application process, the candidate must     pay the required fees directly to the university account.   </li>   <li>     Now, the candidate can proceed ahead with the visa formality and make an     application to the embassy of Uzbekistan.   </li>   <li>     After getting a visa from the Uzbekistan embassy the students can plan their     journey to the beautiful country and start their dream career with FMIPH   </li> </ul>  <h3>Documents required for MBBS study in Uzbekistan</h3>  <p>   To complete the admission process, a candidate requires the following   documents to complete the admission process successfully. </p>  <ul>   <li>Original Indian passport</li>   <li>Scanned self-attested copy of mark sheets and certificate</li>   <li>Invitation letter from FMIPH</li>   <li>Original birth certificate copy</li>   <li>Health and medical certificate</li>   <li>10-15 passport size photo</li> </ul>  <h2>Why is Fergana Medical college the most suitable for Indian students?</h2>  <p>Plenty of benefits are there but only a few are mentioned here.</p> <ul>   <li>Only 6 years of course including 1-year internship</li>   <li>     The MBBS course tuition fee in Uzbekistan is very low. The budget of FMIPH     is around INR 14 Lakh only, which is 4 to 5 times less than the budget of     many private colleges of India.   </li>   <li>     Uzbekistan is one of those countries which is very near to India. Only 3     hours air distance by a direct flight of Uzbek Airways   </li>   <li>Good ratio of Indian students</li>   <li>Perfect balance between theory and practical knowledge</li>   <li>     State of the art library with a collection of Indian writer books and study     material   </li>   <li>Laboratory with 3d simulation&nbsp;</li>   <li>Innovative teaching with 3d human body structures</li>   <li>Indian mess facility with the fine dine-in facility</li>   <li>     Well furnished 2 &amp; 3 seater hostel room with attached bathroom and     modern amenities   </li> </ul>  <h3>   Indian MBBS Students life at Fergana medical institute of Public health,   Uzbekistan </h3>  <p>   &nbsp;Uzbekistan is a country of central Asia, its capital city of Uzbekistan   is Tashkent. The native people of Uzbekistan speak Uzbek and Russian. During   the summers the temperature can move up to 30 &deg;C and -20&deg;C in winters.   Due to this temperature variation the country witnesses very hot summers and   chilling winters. Let&rsquo;s see how Indian students spend their life during   the MBBS course. </p> <ul>   <li>     At FMIPH, professors and faculties come from developed countries with great     experience in their subjects, hence Indian students will get high-quality     education while pursuing the course.   </li>   <li>     University celebrates all the major festivals in all the communities which     makes students belonging to any religion comfortable   </li>   <li>     The university also conducts various events, cultural fest, technical fest     in which students can take part and can exchange their thoughts with     students of other nationality students.   </li>   <li>     For students, there are all facilities under its ultra-modern infrastructure   </li>   <li>     The country is known for its diversity and friendly treatment of foreigners.     They treat the Indian with Love.   </li>   <li>     Students will get the opportunity for exploring the cultural activities     along with their MBBS study.   </li>   <li>     Uzbekistan is known as a traditional country, students here follow their     traditions and stay focused on education   </li>   <li>     Though the local language of Uzbeks but people also speak English, this     makes Indian students live with ease here.   </li>   <li>     Uzbekistan is not very expensive and has well-managed transportation     services which make the students&rsquo; life very comfortable   </li>   <li>     Students can choose to live either in Hostel or they can rent an apartment.     Fergana medical colleges have separate hostels for boys and girls where they     can live with their country mates only.   </li>   <li>     Besides the Indian food facility provided by FMIPH to the students, there     are various restaurants and cafes which serve all the dishes including their     local ones.   </li> </ul>  <h3>Fergana Medical Institute of Public health - New Campus</h3>  <p>   To bring the medical education level of FMIPH to the next level, it has   recently launched a new campus loaded with modern medical equipment and   features. The campus was inaugurated in the presence of Mr. Musaev Behzod   Anvarovich (Minister of the Republic of Uzbekistan) and Mr. Bozarov Zayrullo   Xayitbaevich Hokim (Governor of Fergana city). This new campus will contribute   to the mission of FMIPH to create a technologically rich future for medical   aspirants. </p>', '', ''),
(115, 'SAMARKAND STATE MEDICAL INSTITUTE', 1, '', 7, '<h2>About Samarkand State Medical Institute</h2> <p>   The year 1930 saw the establishment of the State Medical Institute of   Samarkand. One of the country\'s non-profit public higher education institutes,   the Institute is located in Samarkand. The Samarkand State Medical Institute   is highly regarded for its progressive approach to teaching and education. By   creating reforms and implementing changes, the Institute believes in not only   bettering a candidate\'s academic education but also making them more   empathetic towards society and the community as a whole. </p> <p>   Lecture halls, classrooms, and education and clinical laboratories are   equipped with the latest multimedia projectors, video recording, and audio   equipment to ensure quality teaching and research. A distance education   program is also implemented. International connections of the Institute   include Russia, the US, Ukraine, South Korea, and others. In addition to   carrying out projects under grants from the Centre for Science and Technology,   the Samarkand Medical Institute engages in basic research in collaboration   with the Uzbekistan Academy of Sciences. A knowledgeable and experienced staff   is on hand to help students whenever they need it. MBBS aspirants who wish to   learn and grow in the field of medicine will find the Institute to be among   the most desirable educational destinations in recent years due to the   constant improvement of the Institute. </p> <h3>   <strong     >Affiliation and Recognition of Samarkand State Medical Institute</strong   > </h3> <ul>   <li>Recognized by MCI (Medical Council of India)</li>   <li>Recognized by FAIMER</li>   <li>NMC and WHO approved</li>   <li>     Recognized by - United Nations Educational, Scientific and Cultural     Organization (UNESCO)   </li> </ul> <h3><strong>Why Study MBBS at Samarkand State Medical Institute</strong></h3> <ul>   <li>     A major medical Institute in Uzbekistan, Samarkand State Medical Institute     is one of the earliest and most prestigious universities in the country   </li>   <li>WHO and the Medical Council of India have recognized it.</li>   <li>     The Institute boasts a top-notch infrastructure that is technologically     advanced.   </li>   <li>     Medical students have access to multimedia lecture halls and classrooms at     the Institute.   </li>   <li>     An extensive library with internet access and computers is available for     students at the Institute.   </li>   <li>     In addition to print books and information materials, e-books also provide     electronic versions.   </li>   <li>Education is conducted in English.</li>   <li>The tuition fees are affordable and there are loan options available.</li> </ul> <h3>   <strong>Quick highlights about Samarkand State Medical Institute</strong> </h3>  <table>   <tbody>     <tr>       <td>Year of Establishment</td>       <td>1930</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Type</td>       <td>Public</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Recognition</td>       <td>NMC and WHO approved</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Eligibility</td>       <td>         Students should get 50% aggregate in PCB(Physics, Chemistry and Biology)       </td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Course Duration</td>       <td>6 years</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>NEET</td>       <td>Qualifying Marks</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>IELTS/TOFEL</td>       <td>Not Required</td>     </tr>     <tr>       <td>Medium of Teaching</td>       <td>English</td>     </tr>   </tbody> </table>  <h3>   <strong>Advantages of MBBS at Samarkand State Medical Institute</strong> </h3> <ul>   <li>     Samarkand State Medical Institute has a highly qualified and knowledgeable     faculty.   </li>   <li>     A variety of cultural and educational events are held at the Samarkand State     Medical Institute.   </li>   <li>     Several sports competitions are held at the Institute for student-athletes.   </li>   <li>Accommodations are provided to students in the form of hostels.</li>   <li>     The campus is vast, and students can take advantage of its many amenities.   </li>   <li>     Due to the diversity of the student body, students can learn about and     interact with different cultures and values.   </li>   <li>     The Institute does not offer any scholarship programs but does offer a few     scholarships toward the end of the semester to outstanding students.   </li>   <li>     Post-Graduation students can work in hospitals located in Uzbekistan as well     as in any other part of the globe.   </li>   <li>     In accordance with international medical education standards, Samarkand     State Medical Institute has the same curriculum.   </li> </ul> <h3><strong>Duration Of MBBS In Samarkand State Medical Institute</strong></h3> <p>   The&nbsp;MBBS course&nbsp;at Samarkand State Medical Institute is of 6 years. </p> <p><strong>Faculties of Samarkand State Medical Institute</strong></p> <ul>   <li>Faculty of Medical Science</li>   <li>Faculty of Dentistry</li>   <li>Faculty of Nursing</li>   <li>Faculty of Surgery</li>   <li>Faculty of Postgraduate Programs</li>   <li>Faculty of Pharmac</li> </ul>', '', ''),
